rse of my medical studies, including preliminary examinations in botany, zoology, physics, and chemistry, was to become decisive in determining the trend of my literary work.', 74057, 0), (468298, 'In 1973, I left the Rockefeller University to join the Yale University Medical School. The main reason for the move was my belief that the time had come for fruitful interactions between the new discipline of Cell Biology and the traditional fields of interest of medical schools, namely Pathology and Clinical Medicine.', 74058, 0), (468299, 'The problem of chemotherapy of bacterial infections could be solved neither by the experimental medical research worker nor by the chemist alone, but only by the two together working in very close cooperation over many years.', 74059, 0), (468300, 'When I was 10 years old, a cousin of mine took me on a tour of his medical school. And as a special treat, he took me to the pathology lab and took a real human brain out of the jar and placed it in my hands. And there it was, the seat of human consciousness, the powerhouse of the human body, sitting in my hands.', 74060, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468301, 'In a wristwatch, imagine the battery is in the strap and there''s a medical sensor in there connected to the internet. If someone is monitoring that, they could phone up if the user has forgotten to take some medication. This could save hundreds of dollars in medical fees later. What''s missing? It''s a stable battery.', 74061, 0), (468302, 'In 1963 and later papers, I pointed out that the special market characteristics of medical care and medical insurance could be explained by reference to differences in information among the parties involved.', 74062, 0), (468303, 'Alfred Nobel was much concerned, as are we all, with the tangible benefits we hope for and expect from physiological and medical research, and the Faculty of the Caroline Institute has ever been alert to recognize practical benefits.', 74063, 0), (468304, 'Bioethics has hardened into an activist ideology that pervades the medical world, the schools, and government.', 28644, 0), (468305, 'Every year there''s five cop shows, five medical shows and five ''Law & Orders,'' but when it''s a show about women, they want to pit everyone against each other. I don''t think they''d do that if it was a guy show. I think there''s room for all of us.', 74064, 0), (468306, 'I think ''Red Band Society'' is unique because not only is it focusing on a pediatric ward, but it''s from the view from the patient, not from the view of the doctors. So we''re getting to see a whole other side of hospitals and medical series life that we haven''t been able to see before.', 74065, 0), (468307, 'I got the bill for my surgery. Now I know what those doctors were wearing masks for.', 66639, 0), (468308, 'As a physician and as a pilot, I think it lets me be a pretty good translator having one foot in the medical world and one foot in the flying world. Sometimes when the medical guys come in and speak medical stuff to the pilots, the pilots really don''t know what they''re saying.', 74066, 0), (468309, 'My father was a psychiatrist, the medical director of a mental hospital in Scotland, and when I was a student, I took vacation jobs there as a nursing assistant. So I did get to see mental illness, but I don''t remember conversations about mental conditions. My father was a cheerful man with a robust attitude to such things.', 50367, 0), (468310, 'I broke down while at Oxford, was rejected by a record number of medical tribunals during the War, and finally got permission to leave Oxford and do civilian work till the War ended.', 74067, 0), (468311, 'You''re taught from the day you start medical school that you''re a god, that you can have power over life and death. So when your life starts to crumble, and the highest power you see is looking back in the mirror - and you know that power is flawed - it is very hard to get past that.', 35773, 0), (468312, 'When I worked in a medical practice, our practice provided the insurance. When I retired the next day to run for public office to run for Congress, I had to pay first dollar.', 74068, 0), (468313, 'Being a regular in a television series, for me - if I wanted to be a cop, I woulda went to cop school. If I wanted to be a doctor, I would''ve gone to medical school. You get trapped in your normal episodic television shows, basically doing the same thing.', 21381, 0), (468314, 'St. Louis has always been a great center for medicine. It has been a leader in the nation since the early part of the 20th century. Along with that, we''ve been a leader in medical science and biomedical science and innovation in medicine.', 74069, 0), (468315, 'I have a couple of dozen books on my reader: ideal for a long trip or an afternoon waiting at the medical clinic. It''s flexible.', 10542, 0), (468316, 'They don''t like thinking in medical school. They memorize - that''s all they want you to do. You must not think.', 74070, 0), (468317, 'I found out that colonels can stay until they drop dead or get a walker and being a critical medical specialty as an Army trained emergency room doctor, I could stay until age 67.', 74071, 0), (468318, 'We need to bridge the gap between the medical libraries and the hospital rooms; take the information out there already, add to it, focus it, harness it - and bring it to the patient who was just diagnosed today.', 74072, 0), (468319, 'Kids coming back from Iraq and Afghanistan deserve to come back to 21st century medical care.', 74073, 0), (468320, 'Anyone having to do with medicine will have looked at Frank Netter''s art work... I decided I would make him my model... getting my degree in medical illustration and then going on to medical school.', 74074, 0), (468321, 'Some people think that doctors and nurses can put scrambled eggs back in the shell.', 74075, 0), (468322, 'It was clear to me from the start that I would need to combine both a medical degree with a research qualification, to keep at the cutting edge of medical science and technology.', 74076, 0), (468323, 'Sometime they don''t let you know that they know that they don''t know everything, but the core of the medical approach is that you try to identify pathologies, which are subsystems within the human body or the larger system that are having undesirable consequences.', 74077, 0), (468324, 'Truth is everybody is going to hurt you: you just gotta find the ones worth suffering for.', 7, 0), (468325, 'Three things cannot be long hidden: the sun, the moon, and the truth.', 63441, 0), (468326, 'Whoever is careless with the truth in small matters cannot be trusted with important matters.', 104, 0), (468327, 'Honesty is the first chapter in the book of wisdom.', 1207, 0), (468328, 'The truth is you don''t know what is going to happen tomorrow. Life is a crazy ride, and nothing is guaranteed.', 392, 0), (468329, 'Beauty is truth''s smile when she beholds her own face in a perfect mirror.', 430, 0), (468330, 'My parents taught me honesty, truth, compassion, kindness and how to care for people. Also, they encouraged me to take risks, to boldly go. They taught me that the greatest danger in life is not taking the adventure.', 69855, 0), (468331, 'I am the Way, the Truth, and the Life. No one comes to the Father except through me.', 17018, 0), (468332, 'I''m for truth, no matter who tells it. I''m for justice, no matter who it''s for or against.', 1730, 0), (468333, 'There are only two mistakes one can make along the road to truth; not going all the way, and not starting.', 63441, 0), (468334, 'Truth can be stated in a thousand different ways, yet each one can be true.', 1838, 0), (468335, 'Truth stands, even if there be no public support. It is self-sustained.', 32, 0), (468336, 'All truths are easy to understand once they are discovered the point is to discover them. ', 1705, 0), (468337, 'I know where I''m going and I know the truth, and I don''t have to be what you want me to be. I''m free to be what I want.', 1751, 0), (468338, 'The truth is that there is no actual stress or anxiety in the world; it''s your thoughts that create these false beliefs. You can''t package stress, touch it, or see it. There are only people engaged in stressful thinking.', 21729, 0), (468339, 'A liar will not be believed, even when he speaks the truth.', 1733, 0), (468340, 'Have the courage to say no. Have the courage to face the truth. Do the right thing because it is right. These are the magic keys to living your life with integrity.', 3433, 0), (468341, 'It is only with the heart that one can see rightly what is essential is invisible to the eye. ', 69, 0), (468342, 'A lie told often enough becomes the truth.', 2475, 0), (468343, 'It is impossible to struggle for civil rights, equal rights for blacks, without including whites. Because equal rights, fair play, justice, are all like the air: we all have it, or none of us has it. That is the truth of it.', 74, 0), (468344, 'On the mountains of truth you can never climb in vain: either you will reach a point higher up today, or you will be training your powers so that you will be able to climb higher tomorrow.', 11, 0), (468345, 'Once you eliminate the impossible, whatever remains, no matter how improbable, must be the truth.', 764, 0), (468346, 'There''s nothing so kingly as kindness, and nothing so royal as truth.', 45082, 0), (468347, 'There is no greatness where there is no simplicity, goodness and truth.', 93, 0), (468348, 'The greatest truth is honesty, and the greatest falsehood is dishonesty.', 70609, 0), (468349, 'Light is meaningful only in relation to darkness, and truth presupposes error. It is these mingled opposites which people our life, which make it pungent, intoxicating. We only exist in terms of this conflict, in the zone where black and white clash.', 16839, 0), (468350, 'Truth is ever to be found in simplicity, and not in the multiplicity and confusion of things.', 2482, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468351, 'We live in a fantasy world, a world of illusion. The great task in life is to find reality.', 210, 0), (468352, 'I do not know what I may appear to the world, but to myself I seem to have been only like a boy playing on the seashore, and diverting myself in now and then finding a smoother pebble or a prettier shell than ordinary, whilst the great ocean of truth lay all undiscovered before me.', 2482, 0), (468353, 'Truth will ultimately prevail where there is pains to bring it to light.', 3161, 0), (468354, 'Morality is the basis of things and truth is the substance of all morality.', 32, 0), (468355, 'That which is false troubles the heart, but truth brings joyous tranquillity.', 20453, 0), (468356, 'The truth is: Belonging starts with self-acceptance. Your level of belonging, in fact, can never be greater than your level of self-acceptance, because believing that you''re enough is what gives you the courage to be authentic, vulnerable and imperfect.', 247, 0), (468357, 'The only passion that guides me is for the truth... I look at everything from this point of view.', 68679, 0), (468358, '''Beauty is truth, truth beauty,'' - that is all ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.', 191, 0), (468359, 'Peace if possible, truth at all costs.', 1746, 0), (468360, 'The great enemy of the truth is very often not the lie, deliberate, contrived and dishonest, but the myth, persistent, persuasive and unrealistic.', 1680, 0), (468361, 'The word theatre comes from the Greeks. It means the seeing place. It is the place people come to see the truth about life and the social situation.', 19726, 0), (468362, 'Each person does see the world in a different way. There is not a single, unifying, objective truth. We''re all limited by our perspective.', 2777, 0), (468363, 'The object of the superior man is truth.', 819, 0), (468364, 'The sad truth is that the civil rights movement cannot be reborn until we identify the causes of black suffering, some of them self-inflicted. Why can''t black leaders organize rallies around responsible sexuality, birth within marriage, parents reading to their children and students staying in school and doing homework?', 66934, 0), (468365, 'Half a truth is often a great lie.', 1077, 0), (468366, 'I tell you the truth, it is hard for a rich man to enter the kingdom of heaven. Again I tell you, it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of heaven.', 17018, 0), (468367, 'My way of joking is to tell the truth. That''s the funniest joke in the world.', 1751, 0), (468368, 'And we should consider every day lost on which we have not danced at least once. And we should call every truth false which was not accompanied by at least one laugh.', 11, 0), (468369, 'A lot of truth is said in jest.', 392, 0), (468370, 'Reason is the natural order of truth but imagination is the organ of meaning. ', 26, 0), (468371, 'There''s a world of difference between truth and facts. Facts can obscure the truth.', 74, 0), (468372, 'All truth passes through three stages. First, it is ridiculed. Second, it is violently opposed. Third, it is accepted as being self-evident.', 1304, 0), (468373, 'There is some self-interest behind every friendship. There is no friendship without self-interests. This is a bitter truth.', 25555, 0), (468374, 'Plato is my friend; Aristotle is my friend, but my greatest friend is truth.', 2482, 0), (468375, 'Rebellion without truth is like spring in a bleak, arid desert.', 5542, 0), (468376, 'The trouble with lying and deceiving is that their efficiency depends entirely upon a clear notion of the truth that the liar and deceiver wishes to hide.', 2694, 0), (468377, 'Truth is the torch that gleams through the fog without dispelling it.', 13894, 0), (468378, 'If you want to be thought a liar, always tell the truth.', 1014, 0), (468379, 'Facts are many, but the truth is one.', 430, 0), (468380, 'I think the truth is black-and-white.', 74078, 0), (468381, 'My dad raised me with some good advice: ''Always tell the truth. Always shoot from the hip. You might not have many friends, but you''ll never have enemies, because people will always know where you''re coming from.''', 67650, 0), (468382, 'Genocide is not just a murderous madness; it is, more deeply, a politics that promises a utopia beyond politics - one people, one land, one truth, the end of difference. Since genocide is a form of political utopia, it remains an enduring temptation in any multiethnic and multicultural society in crisis.', 16292, 0), (468383, 'By doubting we are led to question, by questioning we arrive at the truth.', 11585, 0), (468384, 'Language is the house of the truth of Being.', 2500, 0), (468385, 'I was born into the world as the king of truth for the salvation of the world.', 63441, 0), (468386, 'To live in the light of a new day and an unimaginable and unpredictable future, you must become fully present to a deeper truth - not a truth from your head, but a truth from your heart; not a truth from your ego, but a truth from the highest source.', 5671, 0), (468387, 'When in doubt tell the truth.', 286, 0), (468388, 'Nothing is more noble, nothing more venerable than fidelity. Faithfulness and truth are the most sacred excellences and endowments of the human mind.', 1306, 0), (468389, 'I''m actually a very honest person, and sometimes I end up like, ''Man, I said too much.'' It''s hard for me not to tell the truth when you ask me.', 22735, 0), (468390, 'There are two ways of lying. One, not telling the truth and the other, making up statistics.', 74079, 0), (468391, 'The earth is supported by the power of truth it is the power of truth that makes the sun shine and the winds blow indeed all things rest upon truth. ', 25555, 0), (468392, 'Non-violence and truth are inseparable and presuppose one another.', 32, 0), (468393, 'The poet is a liar who always speaks the truth.', 2343, 0), (468394, 'Every legend, moreover, contains its residuum of truth, and the root function of language is to control the universe by describing it.', 67562, 0), (468395, 'If there is no criticism, you become lazy. But it should be constructive, and it should be the truth. If it''s biased and there''s no truth in it, then I don''t care about it. If it''s true, it helps me grow.', 66442, 0), (468396, 'I know that some people shy away from what I say. They think it is too blunt, but when you don''t give people that, they feel like you are being fake and you''re not telling the truth. So it''s like, you want me to tell the truth, but when I do, it''s too much for you.', 69257, 0), (468397, 'Most people don''t grow up. It''s too damn difficult. What happens is most people get older. That''s the truth of it. They honor their credit cards, they find parking spaces, they marry, they have the nerve to have children, but they don''t grow up.', 74, 0), (468398, 'The universe is transformation: life is opinion.', 267, 0), (468399, 'Discrimination is a hellhound that gnaws at Negroes in every waking moment of their lives to remind them that the lie of their inferiority is accepted as truth in the society dominating them.', 21767, 0), (468400, 'Clouds and darkness surround us, yet Heaven is just, and the day of triumph will surely come, when justice and truth will be vindicated.', 14327, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468401, 'The truth is, as most of us know, that global warming is real and humans are major contributors, mainly because we wastefully burn fossil fuels.', 13824, 0), (468402, 'Art is a lie that makes us realize truth.', 981, 0), (468403, 'There''s just some magic in truth and honesty and openness.', 22945, 0), (468404, 'The thing about the truth is, not a lot of people can handle it.', 56476, 0), (468405, 'All the truth in the world adds up to one big lie.', 289, 0), (468406, 'Truth, like gold, is to be obtained not by its growth, but by washing away from it all that is not gold.', 93, 0), (468407, 'I never did give anybody hell. I just told the truth and they thought it was hell.', 16121, 0), (468408, 'The truth is not for all men, but only for those who seek it.', 631, 0), (468409, 'Truth is the most valuable thing we have. Let us economize it.', 286, 0), (468410, 'Humanity appreciates truth about as much as a squirrel appreciates silver.', 1508, 0), (468411, 'The lowest form of popular culture - lack of information, misinformation, disinformation, and a contempt for the truth or the reality of most people''s lives - has overrun real journalism. Today, ordinary Americans are being stuffed with garbage.', 17764, 0), (468412, 'Your days are short here; this is the last of your springs. And now in the serenity and quiet of this lovely place, touch the depths of truth, feel the hem of Heaven. You will go away with old, good friends. And don''t forget when you leave why you came.', 69260, 0), (468413, 'There really can be no peace without justice. There can be no justice without truth. And there can be no truth, unless someone rises up to tell you the truth.', 51994, 0), (468414, 'To what greater inspiration and counsel can we turn than to the imperishable truth to be found in this treasure house, the Bible?', 65677, 0), (468415, 'I love new places, new people, new ideas. I love cultural differences, and I''m fascinated by the truth - all the different versions of it.', 69055, 0), (468416, 'The foolish man conceives the idea of ''self.'' The wise man sees there is no ground on which to build the idea of ''self;'' thus, he has a right conception of the world and well concludes that all compounds amassed by sorrow will be dissolved again, but the truth will remain.', 63441, 0), (468417, 'How can sincerity be a condition of friendship? A taste for truth at any cost is a passion which spares nothing.', 532, 0), (468418, 'Say not, ''I have found the truth,'' but rather, ''I have found a truth.''', 5542, 0), (468419, 'The sad truth is that opportunity doesn''t knock twice.', 64979, 0), (468420, 'It''s very easy to be judgmental until you know someone''s truth.', 22748, 0), (468421, 'Truth is so rare that it is delightful to tell it.', 91, 0), (468422, 'Only enemies speak the truth; friends and lovers lie endlessly, caught in the web of duty.', 578, 0), (468423, 'In a controversy the instant we feel anger we have already ceased striving for the truth, and have begun striving for ourselves.', 63441, 0), (468424, 'We cannot forever hide the truth about ourselves, from ourselves.', 9128, 0), (468425, 'You don''t learn from successes you don''t learn from awards you don''t learn from celebrity you only learn from wounds and scars and mistakes and failures. And that''s the truth. ', 64250, 0), (468426, 'The preservation of peace and the guaranteeing of man''s basic freedoms and rights require courage and eternal vigilance: courage to speak and act - and if necessary, to suffer and die - for truth and justice; eternal vigilance, that the least transgression of international morality shall not go undetected and unremedied.', 15968, 0), (468427, 'Even if you are a minority of one, the truth is the truth.', 32, 0), (468428, 'Everyone with a cell phone thinks they''re a photographer. Everyone with a laptop thinks they''re a journalist. But they have no training, and they have no idea of what we keep to in terms of standards, as in what''s far out and what''s reality. And they have no dedication to truth.', 16038, 0), (468429, 'But in truth, should I meet with gold or spices in great quantity, I shall remain till I collect as much as possible, and for this purpose I am proceeding solely in quest of them.', 70809, 0), (468430, 'The truth has never been of any real value to any human being - it is a symbol for mathematicians and philosophers to pursue. In human relations kindness and lies are worth a thousand truths.', 429, 0), (468431, 'The Lord gave me ''Sojourner,'' because I was to travel up an'' down the land, showin'' the people their sins an'' bein'' a sign unto them. Afterwards, I told the Lord I wanted another name ''cause everybody else had two names, and the Lord gave me ''Truth,'' because I was to declare the truth to people.', 2013, 0), (468432, 'You can hate me. You can go out there and say anything you want about me, But you will love me later because I told you the truth.', 47442, 0), (468433, 'The truth is the best picture, the best propaganda.', 67370, 0), (468434, 'That taxes may be the ostensible cause is true, but that they are the true cause is as far remote from truth as light from darkness.', 68658, 0), (468435, 'Truth is a thing immortal and perpetual, and it gives to us a beauty that fades not away in time.', 3411, 0), (468436, 'Truth, like light, blinds. Falsehood, on the contrary, is a beautiful twilight that enhances every object.', 532, 0), (468437, 'There is nothing so strong or safe in an emergency of life as the simple truth.', 96, 0), (468438, 'Everything takes me longer than I expect. It''s the sad truth about life.', 1269, 0), (468439, 'Our cause is just, and the might of Korea that is united with truth is infinite.', 67852, 0), (468440, 'Remember the sufferings of Christ, the storms that were weathered... the crown that came from those sufferings which gave new radiance to the faith... All saints give testimony to 