INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468451, 'You shall know the truth, and the truth shall make you mad.', 1032, 0), (468452, 'It''s a complete lie, why do people buy these papers? It''s not the truth I''m here to say. You know, don''t judge a person, do not pass judgement, unless you have talked to them one on one. I don''t care what the story is, do not judge them because it is a lie.', 646, 0), (468453, 'It is certain that the truth of the Christian faith becomes more evident the more the faith itself is known. Therefore, the doctrine should not only be in Latin but also in the common tongue, and as the faith of the Church is contained in the Scriptures, the more these are known in the true sense, the better.', 50946, 0), (468454, 'It is the nature of truth in general, as of some ores in particular, to be richest when most superficial.', 49, 0), (468455, 'Truth is always strange, stranger than fiction.', 62558, 0), (468456, 'There are only two things. Truth and lies. Truth is indivisible, hence it cannot recognize itself; anyone who wants to recognize it has to be a lie.', 629, 0), (468457, 'The truth is, no one of us can be free until everybody is free.', 74, 0), (468458, 'I was sure I''d set the world on fire, and it was hard for a young feller like me to realize the truth - that I hadn''t set the world on fire, and I was totally unprepared to handle the consequences if ''The Big Trail'' had been a success and launched me as a star.', 25654, 0), (468459, 'The American fascists are most easily recognized by their deliberate perversion of truth and fact. Their newspapers and propaganda carefully cultivate every fissure of disunity, every crack in the common front against fascism.', 17469, 0), (468460, 'I see that the path of progress has never taken a straight line, but has always been a zigzag course amid the conflicting forces of right and wrong, truth and error, justice and injustice, cruelty and mercy.', 69578, 0), (468461, 'In fact men will fight for a superstition quite as quickly as for a living truth - often more so, since a superstition is so intangible you cannot get at it to refute it, but truth is a point of view, and so is changeable.', 30852, 0), (468462, 'The best mind-altering drug is the truth.', 1059, 0), (468463, 'I am sorry to think that you do not get a man''s most effective criticism until you provoke him. Severe truth is expressed with some bitterness.', 1049, 0), (468464, 'When truth has no burning, then it is philosophy, when it gets burning from the heart, it becomes poetry.', 8809, 0), (468465, 'Alas! they had been friends in youth but whispering tongues can poison truth. ', 1910, 0), (468466, 'Tell the children the truth.', 7, 0), (468467, 'I have nothing new to teach the world. Truth and Non-violence are as old as the hills. All I have done is to try experiments in both on as vast a scale as I could.', 32, 0), (468468, 'The truth is, no matter what your lifestyle or occupation, nothing can really stop you when you''re allowing yourself to be exactly who you want to be.', 1029, 0), (468469, 'A day spent without the sight or sound of beauty, the contemplation of mystery, or the search of truth or perfection is a poverty-stricken day; and a succession of such days is fatal to human life.', 13474, 0), (468470, 'Sometimes ideas are coming so fast that I have to stop doing one song to get another. But I don''t forget the first one. If it works, it will always be there. It''s like the truth: it will find you and lift you up. And if it ain''t right, it will dissolve like sand on the beach.', 12819, 0), (468471, 'Materialism coarsens and petrifies everything, making everything vulgar, and every truth false.', 4754, 0), (468472, 'Once you go inside and weed through the muck, you will find the real beauty, the truth about yourself.', 68561, 0), (468473, 'The bud of victory is always in the truth.', 45276, 0), (468474, 'Adversity is the first path to truth.', 62558, 0), (468475, 'We too often bind ourselves by authorities rather than by the truth.', 22250, 0), (468476, 'The theatre was created to tell people the truth about life and the social situation.', 19726, 0), (468477, 'Truth springs from argument amongst friends.', 2498, 0), (468478, 'Truth is weirder than any fiction I''ve seen.', 126, 0), (468479, 'What the imagination seizes as beauty must be truth.', 191, 0), (468480, 'Belief is a wise wager. Granted that faith cannot be proved, what harm will come to you if you gamble on its truth and it proves false? If you gain, you gain all; if you lose, you lose nothing. Wager, then, without hesitation, that He exists.', 144, 0), (468481, 'Why would anyone lie? The truth is always more colorful.', 74080, 0), (468482, 'A thought transfixed me: for the first time in my life, I saw the truth as it is set into song by so many poets, proclaimed as the final wisdom by so many thinkers. The truth - that love is the ultimate and the highest goal to which man can aspire.', 855, 0), (468483, 'Mythology is a subjective truth. Every culture imagines life a certain way.', 12351, 0), (468484, 'The truth is that men are tired of liberty.', 2005, 0), (468485, 'So far as hypotheses are concerned, let no one expect anything certain from astronomy, which cannot furnish it, lest he accept as the truth ideas conceived for another purpose, and depart from this study a greater fool than when he entered it.', 4674, 0), (468486, 'We''re all living in a casino. It''s just Vegas. Everything is on camera. Everything is being recorded. Everything is on audio. The truth is we all have access to everybody else''s information.', 20099, 0), (468487, 'In contradiction and paradox, you can find truth.', 69509, 0), (468488, 'Argument is meant to reveal the truth, not to create it.', 26588, 0), (468489, 'Everything will line up perfectly when knowing and living the truth becomes more important than looking good.', 4680, 0), (468490, 'When virtue is lost, benevolence appears, when benevolence is lost right conduct appears, when right conduct is lost, expedience appears. Expediency is the mere shadow of right and truth; it is the beginning of disorder.', 15, 0), (468491, 'Facts are stubborn things.', 1727, 0), (468492, 'A liar begins with making falsehood appear like truth, and ends with making truth itself appear like falsehood.', 63810, 0), (468493, 'I perceived how that it was impossible to establish the lay people in any truth except the Scripture were plainly laid before their eyes in their mother tongue.', 44167, 0), (468494, 'Attempting to get at truth means rejecting stereotypes and cliches.', 74081, 0), (468495, 'The single overriding objective in wellness is creating constant personal renewal where we recognize and act on the truth that each day is a miraculous gift, and our job is to untie the ribbons. That''s the Law of Esprit: living life with joy.', 54064, 0), (468496, 'The essential truth is that sometimes you''re worried that they''ll find out it''s a fluke, that you don''t really have it. You''ve lost the muse or - the worst dread - you never had it at all. I went through all that madness early on.', 2185, 0), (468497, 'Two qualities are indispensable: first, an intellect that, even in the darkest hour, retains some glimmerings of the inner light which leads to truth; and second, the courage to follow this faint light wherever it may lead.', 2677, 0), (468498, 'Legends die hard. They survive as truth rarely does.', 4743, 0), (468499, 'This is the truth: as from a fire aflame thousands of sparks come forth, even so from the Creator an infinity of beings have life and to him return again.', 1306, 0), (468500, 'No human being is constituted to know the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth; and even the best of men must be content with fragments, with partial glimpses, never the full fruition.', 3668, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468501, 'You never monkey with the truth.', 61742, 0), (468502, 'A writer should have this little voice inside of you saying, Tell the truth. Reveal a few secrets here.', 1484, 0), (468503, 'Truth suffers from too much analysis.', 1265, 0), (468504, 'Friendship at first sight, like love at first sight, is said to be the only truth.', 2584, 0), (468505, 'If there were only one truth, you couldn''t paint a hundred canvases on the same theme.', 981, 0), (468506, 'I do not know what I may appear to the world; but to myself, I seem to have been only like a boy playing on the seashore, and diverting myself now and then in finding a smoother pebble or prettier shell than ordinary, while the great ocean of truth lay all undiscovered before me.', 2482, 0), (468507, 'In the consciousness of the truth he has perceived, man now sees everywhere only the awfulness or the absurdity of existence and loathing seizes him.', 11, 0), (468508, 'Myths and creeds are heroic struggles to comprehend the truth in the world.', 1347, 0), (468509, 'Now all we need is to continue to speak the truth fearlessly, and we shall add to our number those who will turn the scale to the side of equal and full justice in all things.', 63996, 0), (468510, 'One of the grand fundamental principles of Mormonism is to receive truth, let it come from whence it may.', 3554, 0), (468511, 'Every truth has two sides; it is as well to look at both, before we commit ourselves to either.', 1733, 0), (468512, 'There are sadistic scientists who hurry to hunt down errors instead of establishing the truth.', 1036, 0), (468513, 'We must never be afraid to go too far, for truth lies beyond.', 450, 0), (468514, 'The great advantage about telling the truth is that nobody ever believes it.', 3165, 0), (468515, 'I am a firm believer in the people. If given the truth, they can be depended upon to meet any national crisis. The great point is to bring them the real facts.', 1012, 0), (468516, 'Truth is always served by great minds, even if they fight it.', 3404, 0), (468517, 'Without accepting the fact that everything changes, we cannot find perfect composure. Unfortunately, although it is true, it is difficult for us to accept it. Because we cannot accept the truth of transience, we suffer.', 2504, 0), (468518, 'Truth is confirmed by inspection and delay falsehood by haste and uncertainty. ', 3582, 0), (468519, 'Mystical explanations are thought to be deep the truth is that they are not even shallow. ', 11, 0), (468520, 'I believe that one key to success is to accept truth, no matter how it''s spoken.', 66592, 0), (468521, 'Time is money says the proverb, but turn it around and you get a precious truth. Money is time.', 5990, 0), (468522, 'It is a melancholy truth that even great men have their poor relations.', 96, 0), (468523, 'People can choose between the sweet lie or the bitter truth. I say the bitter truth, but many people don''t want to hear it.', 72969, 0), (468524, 'Truth is a great flirt.', 22699, 0), (468525, 'There is nothing so powerful as truth, and often nothing so strange.', 3308, 0), (468526, 'Great is truth, but still greater, from a practical point of view, is silence about truth. By simply not mentioning certain subjects... totalitarian propagandists have influenced opinion much more effectively than they could have by the most eloquent denunciations.', 1032, 0), (468527, 'It does not require many words to speak the truth.', 4664, 0), (468528, 'Marilyn Monroe wasn''t even her real name, Charles Manson isn''t his real name, and now, I''m taking that to be my real name. But what''s real? You can''t find the truth, you just pick the lie you like the best.', 2519, 0), (468529, 'Truth is the daughter of time, and I feel no shame in being her midwife.', 13386, 0), (468530, 'We all know that Art is not truth. Art is a lie that makes us realize the truth, at least the truth that is given to us to understand.', 981, 0), (468531, 'Expectations are a form of first-class truth: If people believe it, it''s true.', 1133, 0), (468532, 'Plato is dear to me, but dearer still is truth.', 1116, 0), (468533, 'I don''t believe it. Prove it to me and I still won''t believe it.', 386, 0), (468534, 'If you shut up truth, and bury it underground, it will but grow.', 1019, 0), (468535, 'Sometimes the truth hurts. And sometimes it feels real good.', 68, 0), (468536, 'The truth will set you free, but first it will make you miserable.', 44653, 0), (468537, 'There are some people so addicted to exaggeration that they can''t tell the truth without lying.', 3355, 0), (468538, 'The opposite of a fact is falsehood, but the opposite of one profound truth may very well be another profound truth.', 2826, 0), (468539, 'For my part, whatever anguish of spirit it may cost, I am willing to know the whole truth; to know the worst and provide for it.', 3269, 0), (468540, 'The water in a vessel is sparkling the water in the sea is dark. The small truth has words which are clear the great truth has great silence. ', 430, 0), (468541, 'Truth is certainly a branch of morality and a very important one to society.', 1207, 0), (468542, 'The truth is, I''ve never fooled anyone. I''ve let men sometimes fool themselves.', 1, 0), (468543, 'You don''t have to sort of enhance reality. There is nothing stranger than truth.', 58263, 0), (468544, 'The truth is, we''re all cyborgs with cell phones and online identities.', 2219, 0), (468545, 'I am amazed about how everyone wants to know about my love life. They whisper to me, ''Tell me the truth? Is it true?'' Who cares? Because we have this job, we are to say to everybody what we do, or with whom we sleep? It''s a bit absurd, but that''s why everybody lies so much.', 68266, 0), (468546, 'It is by doubting that we come to investigate, and by investigating that we recognize the truth.', 11585, 0), (468547, 'When governments rely increasingly on sophisticated public relations agencies, public debate disappears and is replaced by competing propaganda campaigns, with all the accompanying deceits. Advertising isn''t about truth or fairness or rationality, but about mobilising deeper and more primitive layers of the human mind.', 18504, 0), (468548, 'Truth cannot be brought down; rather, the individual must make the effort to ascend to it. You cannot bring the mountaintop to the valley. If you would attain to the mountaintop, you must pass through the valley, climb the steeps, unafraid of the dangerous precipices.', 1780, 0), (468549, 'After all, the ultimate goal of all research is not objectivity, but truth.', 72887, 0), (468550, 'Seldom, very seldom, does complete truth belong to any human disclosure; seldom can it happen that something is not a little disguised, or a little mistaken.', 24, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468551, 'Go to the truth beyond the mind. Love is the bridge.', 3366, 0), (468552, 'Without the way, there is no going; without the truth, there is no knowing; without the life, there is no living.', 946, 0), (468553, 'The truth is I love being alive. And I love feeling free. So if I can''t have those things then I feel like a caged animal and I''d rather not be in a cage. I''d rather be dead. And it''s real simple. And I think it''s not that uncommon.', 1380, 0), (468554, 'I guess rumors are more exciting than the truth.', 37889, 0), (468555, 'So near is falsehood to truth that a wise man would do well not to trust himself on the narrow edge.', 1306, 0), (468556, 'Competence, like truth, beauty, and contact lenses, is in the eye of the beholder.', 2120, 0), (468557, 'Falsehood has an infinity of combinations, but truth has only one mode of being.', 1372, 0), (468558, 'Intense feeling too often obscures the truth.', 16121, 0), (468559, 'Exaggeration is truth that has lost its temper.', 5542, 0), (468560, 'Buonaparte has often made his boast that our fleet would be worn out by keeping the sea and that his was kept in order and increasing by staying in port; but know he finds, I fancy, if Emperors hear the truth, that his fleet suffers more in a night than ours in one year.', 20802, 0), (468561, 'We all have a social mask, right? We put it on, we go out, put our best foot forward, our best image. But behind that social mask is a personal truth, what we really, really believe about who we are and what we''re capable of.', 68937, 0), (468562, 'I am not afraid of the pen, or the scaffold, or the sword. I will tell the truth wherever I please.', 65862, 0), (468563, 'Art is magic delivered from the lie of being truth.', 18848, 0), (468564, 'Because the truth is, today''s immigrants, as they have for generation after generation, work the longest hours at the hardest jobs for the lowest pay, jobs that are just about impossible to fill.', 67343, 0), (468565, 'The truth doesn''t have to do with cruelty, the truth has to do with mercy.', 1601, 0), (468566, 'Piety requires us to honor truth above our friends.', 1116, 0), (468567, 'The color of truth is gray.', 8, 0), (468568, 'Most jokes state a bitter truth.', 51804, 0), (468569, 'Everyone who knows me will know the truth, which is that my children come first in my life and that I would never harm any child.', 646, 0), (468570, 'The key to wisdom is this - constant and frequent questioning, for by doubting we are led to question and by questioning we arrive at the truth.', 11585, 0), (468571, 'I am certain of nothing but the holiness of the heart''s affections, and the truth of imagination.', 191, 0), (468572, 'There are, in truth, no specialties in medicine, since to know fully many of the most important diseases a man must be familiar with their manifestations in many organs.', 3668, 0), (468573, 'The pillars of truth and the pillars of freedom - they are the pillars of society.', 845, 0), (468574, 'When you want to fool the world, tell the truth.', 4746, 0), (468575, 'Nothing is beautiful, only man: on this piece of naivete rests all aesthetics, it is the first truth of aesthetics. Let us immediately add its second: nothing is ugly but degenerate man - the domain of aesthetic judgment is therewith defined.', 11, 0), (468576, 'Memory is a complicated thing, a relative to truth, but not its twin.', 679, 0), (468577, 'One may preach a covenant of grace more clearly than another... But when they preach a covenant of works for salvation, that is not truth.', 66838, 0), (468578, 'We don''t go into journalism to be popular. It is our job to seek the truth and put constant pressure on our leaders until we get answers.', 16038, 0), (468579, 'When we believe in lies, we cannot see the truth, so we make thousands of assumptions and we take them as truth. One of the biggest assumptions we make is that the lies we believe are the truth!', 67703, 0), (468580, 'The discovery of truth is prevented more effectively, not by the false appearance things present and which mislead into error, not directly by weakness of the reasoning powers, but by preconceived opinion, by prejudice.', 1304, 0), (468581, 'It is hard to believe that a man is telling the truth when you know that you would lie if you were in his place.', 411, 0), (468582, 'I tore myself away from the safe comfort of certainties through my love for truth - and truth rewarded me.', 477, 0), (468583, 'Truth in philosophy means that concept and external reality correspond.', 2787, 0), (468584, 'A rusty nail placed near a faithful compass, will sway it from the truth, and wreck the argosy.', 972, 0), (468585, 'In our development, as we grow throughout our lives, the structure of our beliefs becomes very complicated, and we make it even more complicated because we make the assumption that what we believe is the absolute truth.', 67703, 0), (468586, 'Truth made you a traitor as it often does in a time of scoundrels.', 1991, 0), (468587, 'I remember how being young and black and gay and lonely felt. A lot of it was fine, feeling I had the truth and the light and the key, but a lot of it was purely hell.', 897, 0), (468588, 'There are new words now that excuse everybody. Give me the good old days of heroes and villains, the people you can bravo or hiss. There was a truth to them that all the slick credulity of today cannot touch.', 13058, 0), (468589, 'Never wear your best trousers when you go out to fight for freedom and truth.', 845, 0), (468590, 'We should consider every day lost on which we have not danced at least once. And we should call every truth false which was not accompanied by at least one laugh.', 11, 0), (468591, 'No one can look back on his schooldays and say with truth that they were altogether unhappy.', 521, 0), (468592, 'In everything truth surpasses the imitation and copy.', 1306, 0), (468593, 'I try to lie as much as I can when I''m interviewed. It''s reverse psychology. I figure if you lie, they''ll print the truth.', 3877, 0), (468594, 'Humans love truth and justice, and rejoice in ceremonies that honor those qualities. For that sentiment we should indeed thank God.', 71981, 0), (468595, 'I am a lover of truth, a worshipper of freedom, a celebrant at the altar of language and purity and tolerance.', 1031, 0), (468596, 'In matters of truth and justice, there is no difference between large and small problems, for issues concerning the treatment of people are all the same.', 104, 0), (468597, 'There are only two people who can tell you the truth about yourself - an enemy who has lost his temper and a friend who loves you dearly.', 63363, 0), (468598, 'Truth is beautiful, without doubt; but so are lies.', 760, 0), (468599, 'The words of truth are always paradoxical.', 15, 0), (468600, 'Cynicism is an unpleasant way of saying the truth.', 1991, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468601, 'An error does not become truth by reason of multiplied propagation, nor does truth become error because nobody sees it.', 32, 0), (468602, 'The sad truth is that excellence makes people nervous.', 28348, 0), (468603, 'Truth gets well if she is run over by a locomotive, while error dies of lockjaw if she scratches her finger.', 70801, 0), (468604, 'It becomes more necessary to see the truth as it is if you realize that the only vehicle for change are these people who have lost their personality.', 66913, 0), (468605, 'Gossip needn''t be false to be evil - there''s a lot of truth that shouldn''t be passed around.', 27528, 0), (468606, 'Most people think that shadows follow, precede or surround beings or objects. The truth is that they also surround words, ideas, desires, deeds, impulses and memories.', 10, 0), (468607, 'You will find truth more quickly through delight than gravity. Let out a little more string on your kite.', 4680, 0), (468608, 'Tragedy is like strong acid - it dissolves away all but the very gold of truth.', 178, 0), (468609, 'When we say ''less fortunate,'' we generally mean the poor rather than the disabled, who actually are less fortunate. In truth, the poor are generally ''less fortunate'' only in terms of genetics. They are certainly not less fortunate in the amount of help they receive.', 17797, 0), (468610, 'Truth is the cry of all, but the game of few.', 43455, 0), (468611, 'When you''re caught up in the storm or, you know, just the turmoil of everything that there is another side and you do get through it. And you know, just standing by the truth and doing the right thing.', 74082, 0), (468612, 'The truth is that we don''t need everyone to like us we need a few people to love us. Because what''s better than being roundly liked is being fully known - an impossibility both professionally and personally if you''re so busy being likable that you forget to be yourself. ', 18056, 0), (468613, 'I''ve studied pathological liars, and anything they say, they believe, and that''s one of the reasons they''re so convincing, because they have no connection with the truth. It''s a dead issue. It''s like they''re color-blind to the truth. So anything that comes out of their mouths is their reality.', 69506, 0), (468614, 'Everything deep is also simple and can be reproduced simply as long as its reference to the whole truth is maintained. But what matters is not what is witty but what is true.', 1006, 0), (468615, 'The most powerful element in advertising is the truth.', 66741, 0), (468616, 'To be outspoken is easy when you do not wait to speak the complete truth.', 430, 0), (468617, 'Words are but symbols for the relations of things to one another and to us nowhere do they touch upon absolute truth. ', 11, 0), (468618, 'Because no matter what you say in life, the truth will always be the truth. You know when someone is telling the truth, you look in the eyes. I have a tendency to believe people.', 69380, 0), (468619, 'There''s a gap somehow between empathy and activism. Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. spoke of ''soul force'' - something that emanates from a deep truth inside of us and empowers us to act. Once you identify your inner genius, you will be able to take action, whether it''s writing a check or digging a well.', 723, 0), (468620, 'You''re not going to be liked by everybody when you speak the truth. I don''t speak the truth to put people down I don''t speak the truth to show disrespect. ', 29415, 0), (468621, 'Matangi''s mantra is aim, which is MIA backwards. She fights for freedom of speech and stands for truth, and lives in the ghetto because her dad was the first person in Hindu mythology who came from the ''hood, but had gained enlightenment through not being a Brahmin.', 67100, 0), (468622, 'When I tell the truth, it is not for the sake of convincing those who do not know it, but for the sake of defending those that do.', 221, 0), (468623, 'But now I have come to believe that the whole world is an enigma, a harmless enigma that is made terrible by our own mad attempt to interpret it as though it had an underlying truth.', 736, 0), (468624, 'Life is the game that must be played, this truth at least, good friends, we know; so live and laugh, nor be dismayed as one by one the phantoms go.', 2523, 0), (468625, 'The truth is often a terrible weapon of aggression. It is possible to lie, and even to murder, with the truth.', 29457, 0), (468626, 'When truth is no longer free, freedom is no longer real: the truths of the police are the truths of today.', 5866, 0), (468627, 'Truth may be stretched, but cannot be broken, and always gets above falsehood, as does oil above water.', 62284, 0), (468628, 'To tell the truth is to become beautiful, to begin to love yourself, value yourself. And that''s political, in its most profound way.', 8754, 0), (468629, 'If you''re going to tell people the truth, be funny or they''ll kill you.', 22666, 0), (468630, 'If now isn''t a good time for the truth I don''t see when we''ll get to it.', 491, 0), (468631, 'To me a real patriot is like a real friend. Who''s your real friend? It''s the person who tells you the truth. That''s who my real friends are. So, you know, I think as far as our country goes, we need more people who will do that.', 2460, 0), (468632, 'Truth never yet fell dead in the streets; it has such affinity with the soul of man, the seed however broadcast will catch somewhere and produce its hundredfold.', 1771, 0), (468633, 'Truth lies within a little and certain compass, but error is immense.', 71982, 0), (468634, 'The search for the truth is the most important work in the whole world, and the most dangerous.', 10566, 0), (468635, 'Truth is simply a compliment paid to sentences seen to be paying their way.', 74083, 0), (468636, 'It is one thing to show a man that he is in an error, and another to put him in possession of the truth.', 2375, 0), (468637, 'Deconstruction insists not that truth is illusory but that it is institutional.', 1914, 0), (468638, 'Such truth, as opposeth no man''s profit, nor pleasure, is to all men welcome.', 2593, 0), (468639, 'People think SEALs are cold-blooded, heartless, wound-up, brainwashed killers. They imagine you can just point a SEAL in a direction and say, ''Go kill.'' The truth is you''re talking about a bunch of kind-hearted, jovial guys. The only thing that separates them is mental toughness.', 67461, 0), (468640, 'The pharmaceutical industry likes to depict itself as a research-based industry, as the source of innovative drugs. Nothing could be further from the truth. This is their incredible PR and their nerve.', 4691, 0), (468641, 'Dear Internet: You are very good at spreading rumors. Truth is more valuable and much harder to come by.', 13072, 0), (468642, 'Truth is mysterious, elusive, always to be conquered. Liberty is dangerous, as hard to live with as it is elating. We must march toward these two goals, painfully but resolutely, certain in advance of our failings on so long a road.', 532, 0), (468643, 'You don''t have to be scared of me, because I am loyal. Why are people so scared of creative ideas and so scared of truth? All I want to do is do good.', 3290, 0), (468644, 'Truth is so much more interesting than the fiction we''re used to.', 11629, 0), (468645, 'I believe in people. Human beings, deep down, are essentially good. Any jury can filter through whatever bull might be thrown their way and use common sense to get to the truth of a case. Juries make the right decisions, almost unfailingly, because people know right from wrong.', 67858, 0), (468646, 'As scarce as truth is, the supply has always been in excess of the demand.', 3355, 0), (468647, 'All truth is simple... is that not doubly a lie?', 11, 0), (468648, 'The truth is that Oxford is simply a very beautiful city in which it is convenient to segregate a certain number of the young of the nation while they are growing up.', 399, 0), (468649, 'Champagne, if you are seeking the truth, is better than a lie detector. It encourages a man to be expansive, even reckless, while lie detectors are only a challenge to tell lies successfully.', 429, 0), (468650, 'And, after all, what is a lie? ''Tis but the truth in a masquerade.', 3348, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468651, 'Truth is a good dog; but always beware of barking too close to the heels of an error, lest you get your brains kicked out.', 1035, 0), (468652, 'Art, whose honesty must work through artifice, cannot avoid cheating truth.', 809, 0), (468653, 'A good man often appears gauche simply because he does not take advantage of the myriad mean little chances of making himself look stylish. Preferring truth to form, he is not constantly at work upon the facade of his appearance.', 21687, 0), (468654, 'Let my name stand among those who are willing to bear ridicule and reproach for the truth''s sake, and so earn some right to rejoice when the victory is won.', 296, 0), (468655, 'In seeking truth you have to get both sides of a story.', 9501, 0), (468656, 'Justice is the truth in action.', 8895, 0), (468657, 'It is proof of a base and low mind for one to wish to think with the masses or majority, merely because the majority is the majority. Truth does not change because it is, or is not, believed by a majority of the people.', 2882, 0), (468658, 'It is only a man''s own fundamental thoughts that have truth and life in them. For it is these that he really and completely understands. To read the thoughts of others is like taking the remains of someone else''s meal, like putting on the discarded clothes of a stranger.', 1304, 0), (468659, 'Search for the truth is the noblest occupation of man its publication is a duty. ', 62704, 0), (468660, 'Every mind must make its choice between truth and repose. It cannot have both.', 760, 0), (468661, 'Truth is mighty and will prevail. There is nothing wrong with this, except that it ain''t so.', 286, 0), (468662, 'Liberals should not overplay this weapons of mass destruction card, because you want me to tell you the truth? Most of us are not going to care if they don''t find these weapons of mass destruction. It''s enough for a lot of us to see those kids smiling on that street again.', 28316, 0), (468663, 'I think it better that in times like these a poet''s mouth be silent, for in truth we have no gift to set a statesman right.', 62867, 0), (468664, 'Truth is immortal error is mortal. ', 5264, 0), (468665, 'Opinions are made to be changed - or how is truth to be got at?', 62558, 0), (468666, 'Madness is the absolute break with the work of art; it forms the constitutive moment of abolition, which dissolves in time the truth of the work of art.', 833, 0), (468667, 'Men are apt to prefer a prosperous error to an afflicted truth.', 3943, 0), (468668, 'I think there ought to be a club in which preachers and journalists could come together and have the sentimentalism of the one matched with the cynicism of the other. That ought to bring them pretty close to the truth.', 1779, 0), (468669, 'If you shut the door to all errors, truth will be shut out.', 430, 0), (468670, 'If there is one eternal truth of politics, it is that there are always a dozen good reasons for doing nothing.', 5956, 0), (468671, 'Personality is only ripe when a man has made the truth his own.', 3131, 0), (468672, 'You know what the Englishman''s idea of compromise is? He says, Some people say there is a God. Some people say there is no God. The truth probably lies somewhere between these two statements.', 62867, 0), (468673, 'The truth is that neither British nor American imperialism was or is idealistic. It has always been driven by economic or strategic interests.', 65031, 0), (468674, 'To be afraid is to behave as if the truth were not true.', 51917, 0), (468675, 'I''m one of those people you hate because of genetics. It''s the truth.', 2614, 0), (468676, 'In the computer field, the moment of truth is a running program; all else is prophecy.', 2920, 0), (468677, 'I can prove anything by statistics except the truth.', 62800, 0), (468678, 'Children say that people are hung sometimes for speaking the truth.', 63110, 0), (468679, 'The entrance into Jerusalem has all the elements of the theatre of the absurd: the poor king truth comes riding on a donkey symbolic actions - even parading without a permit! ', 43234, 0), (468680, 'I think Hollywood has a class system. The actors are like the inmates, but the truth is they''re running the asylum.', 29124, 0), (468681, 'Let us hold our discussion together in our own persons, making trial of the truth and of ourselves.', 45582, 0), (468682, 'Truth is inseperable from the illusory belief that from the figures of the unreal one day, in spite of all, real deliverance will come.', 18848, 0), (468683, 'Truth, at the wrong time, can be dangerous.', 732, 0), (468684, 'So that godly sorrow may be discerned by this train of graces wherewith it is accompanied, that worldly sorrow wants, at least in the truth of them, though it may have some shadows of them.', 72948, 0), (468685, 'To expect the world to receive a new truth, or even an old truth, without challenging it, is to look for one of those miracles which do not occur.', 43909, 0), (468686, 'Truth is born into this world only with pangs and tribulations, and every fresh truth is received unwillingly.', 43909, 0), (468687, 'No matter how difficult and painful it may be, nothing sounds as good to the soul as the truth.', 29471, 0), (468688, 'Eternal truth, eternal righteousness, eternal love; these only can triumph, for these only can endure.', 68027, 0), (468689, 'I have discovered the art of deceiving diplomats. I tell them the truth and they never believe me.', 63883, 0), (468690, 'The oblique paradox of propaganda is that the lie in the throat becomes, by repetition, the truth in the heart.', 67254, 0), (468691, 'Poetry is a political act because it involves telling the truth.', 8754, 0), (468692, 'If you come to a negotiation table saying you have the final truth, that you know nothing but the truth and that is final, you will get nothing.', 74084, 0), (468693, 'The truth doesn''t hurt unless it ought to.', 14130, 0), (468694, 'Exactitude is not truth.', 4050, 0), (468695, 'Uniform ideas originating among entire peoples unknown to each other must have a common ground of truth.', 74085, 0), (468696, 'When a truth is not given complete freedom, freedom is not complete.', 1412, 0), (468697, 'A half truth, like half a brick, is always more forcible as an argument than a whole one. It carries better.', 9981, 0), (468698, 'The truth is, I''m proud of the life I''ve lived so far, and though I''ve made my share of mistakes, I have no regrets.', 66662, 0), (468699, 'The immediate future is going to be tragic for all of us unless we find a way of making the vast educational resources of this country serve the true purpose of education, truth and justice.', 69118, 0), (468700, 'There are various eyes. Even the Sphinx has eyes: and as a result there are various truths, and as a result there is no truth.', 11, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468701, 'Truth is a demure lady, much too ladylike to knock you on your head and drag you to her cave. She is there, but people must want her, and seek her out.', 64070, 0), (468702, 'Man can embody truth but he cannot know it.', 62867, 0), (468703, 'It''s essential to tell the truth at all times. This will reduce life''s pain. Lying distorts reality. All forms of distorted thinking must be corrected.', 10624, 0), (468704, 'Truth lives, in fact, for the most part on a credit system. Our thoughts and beliefs pass, so long as nothing challenges them, just as bank-notes pass so long as nobody refuses them.', 1782, 0), (468705, 'There are also two kinds of truths: truth of reasoning and truths of fact. Truths of reasoning are necessary and their opposite is impossible those of fact are contingent and their opposite is possible. ', 70838, 0), (468706, 'The stupid believe that to be truthful is easy; only the artist, the great artist, knows how difficult it is.', 307, 0), (468707, 'Though the names karma yoga and sannyasa are different, the truth at the heart of both is the same.', 74086, 0), (468708, 'If the Republicans will stop telling lies about the Democrats, we will stop telling the truth about them.', 69260, 0), (468709, 'It is a clear truth that those who every day barter away other men''s liberty will soon care little for their own.', 16822, 0), (468710, 'Instead of generating either unnecessary alarm or a false sense of security regarding these fundamental issues, the best course is to empower people with the truth.', 74087, 0), (468711, 'Scientific truth is marvelous, but moral truth is divine and whoever breathes its air and walks by its light has found the lost paradise.', 2053, 0), (468712, 'Sex is full of lies. The body tries to tell the truth. But, it''s usually too battered with rules to be heard, and bound with pretenses so it can hardly move. We cripple ourselves with lies.', 216, 0), (468713, 'A truth that''s told with bad intent beats all the lies you can invent.', 221, 0), (468714, 'I am in the present. I cannot know what tomorrow will bring forth. I can know only what the truth is for me today. That is what I am called upon to serve, and I serve it in all lucidity.', 16868, 0), (468715, 'Scarce any problem will appear more hard and difficult, than that of determining the distance of the Sun from the Earth very near the truth: but even this... will without much labour be effected.', 57694, 0), (468716, 'Truth is a tendency.', 11496, 0), (468717, 'Wine comes in at the mouth And love comes in at the eye That''s all we shall know for truth Before we grow old and die. ', 62867, 0), (468718, 'The truth doesn''t change. It was the same when Moses got the Ten Commandments as it is today. That''s the thing about the truth. That''s the thing about real. It doesn''t change and it doesn''t have to change. Now you can put it in a different book, but it''s still real. It''s still the truth.', 67702, 0), (468719, 'When you buy into the cultural idea of what''s acceptable and unacceptable, you reinforce negative stereotypes and prejudices. That wouldn''t work for me. I don''t love to give advice to anyone, because we all have to make our own choices, but I''d want to live my life in truth.', 37611, 0), (468720, 'The art of storytelling is reaching its end because the epic side of truth, wisdom, is dying out.', 579, 0), (468721, 'The pursuit of truth does not permit violence on one''s opponent.', 32, 0), (468722, 'Man will occasionally stumble over the truth, but most of the time he will pick himself up and continue on.', 3621, 0), (468723, 'In nonfiction, you have that limitation, that constraint, of telling the truth.', 1651, 0), (468724, 'Mention the gothic, and many readers will probably picture gloomy castles and an assortment of sinister Victoriana. However, the truth is that the gothic genre has continued to flourish and evolve since the days of Bram Stoker, producing some of its most interesting and accomplished examples in the 20th century - in literature, film and beyond.', 252, 0), (468725, 'What is the difference between unethical and ethical advertising? Unethical advertising uses falsehoods to deceive the public ethical advertising uses truth to deceive the public. ', 74088, 0), (468726, 'Dispassionate objectivity is itself a passion, for the real and for the truth.', 62519, 0), (468727, 'The lawyer''s truth is not Truth, but consistency or a consistent expediency.', 1049, 0), (468728, 'Let me get you to understand I don''t bully anybody. I stand up for what I believe in and I''m very honest and I always tell the truth. I''m not a liar, I''m not manipulative and I don''t stab you in your back because I will stab you in your chest.', 69062, 0), (468729, 'Art is not a study of positive reality, it is the seeking for ideal truth.', 485, 0), (468730, 'A lie which is half a truth is ever the blackest of lies.', 63203, 0), (468731, 'Truth is tough. It will not break, like a bubble, at a touch; nay, you may kick it about all day like a football, and it will be round and full at evening.', 24754, 0), (468732, 'The truth. It is a beautiful and terrible thing, and must therefore be treated with great caution.', 28, 0), (468733, 'I am saddened by how people treat one another and how we are so shut off from one another and how we judge one another, when the truth is, we are all one connected thing. We are all from the same exact molecules.', 1217, 0), (468734, 'We are the United States of Amnesia, which is encouraged by a media that has no desire to tell us the truth about anything, serving their corporate masters who have other plans to dominate us.', 2074, 0), (468735, 'The truth is, I can never die. For I will be in everything and see you in everything and watch over you. I am your reaction in the water of a mountain lake.', 34061, 0), (468736, 'Without free speech no search for truth is possible... no discovery of truth is useful.', 30815, 0), (468737, 'I used to be more paranoid and stressed, constantly worrying about my Plan B. But the truth is I don''t have one.', 69155, 0), (468738, 'No one can be happy who has been thrust outside the pale of truth. And there are two ways that one can be removed from this realm: by lying, or by being lied to.', 65434, 0), (468739, 'I wanted to write about the moment when your addictions no longer hide the truth from you. When your whole life breaks down. That''s the moment when you have to somehow choose what your life is going to be about.', 30, 0), (468740, 'Truth is something which can''t be told in a few words. Those who simplify the universe only reduce the expansion of its meaning.', 23, 0), (468741, 'That which you create in beauty and goodness and truth lives on for all time to come. Don''t spend your life accumulating material objects that will only turn to dust and ashes.', 1391, 0), (468742, 'In order to maintain an untenable position, you have to be actively ignorant. One motto on the show is, ''Keep your facts, I''m going with the truth.''', 1450, 0), (468743, 'I guess, to tell you the truth, I''ve never had much of a desire to grow facial hair. I think I''ve managed to play quarterback just fine without a mustache.', 12973, 0), (468744, 'Myth and fairy-story must, as all art, reflect and contain in solution elements of moral and religious truth (or error), but not explicit, not in the known form of the primary ''real'' world.', 65, 0), (468745, 'There''s something uniquely exhilarating about puzzling together the truth at the hands of an unreliable narrator.', 6299, 0), (468746, 'As someone who specializes in deception, I''ll tell you this much: When someone insistently implores, ''Believe me,'' don''t. Pleading ''believe me'' or ''trust me'' - insisting to people that you are telling the truth - is a tell-tale sign that you probably aren''t.', 73298, 0), (468747, 'We are not afraid to entrust the American people with unpleasant facts, foreign ideas, alien philosophies, and competitive values. For a nation that is afraid to let its people judge the truth and falsehood in an open market is a nation that is afraid of its people.', 1680, 0), (468748, 'The truth is lived, not taught.', 305, 0), (468749, 'Not every truth is the better for showing its face undisguised and often silence is the wisest thing for a man to heed. ', 16113, 0), (468750, 'Clarity and consistency are not enough: the quest for truth requires humility and effort.', 4710, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468751, 'Sincerity is moral truth.', 41950, 0), (468752, 'I''m always pursuing the next dream, hunting for the next truth.', 74089, 0), (468753, 'Truth indeed rather alleviates than hurts, and will always bear up against falsehood, as oil does above water.', 62284, 0), (468754, 'But truth is most likely to be exhibited by the general sense of contemporaries, when the feelings of the heart can be expressed without suffering itself to be disguised by the prejudices of man.', 70796, 0), (468755, 'Truth is the beginning of every good to the gods, and of every good to man.', 51, 0), (468756, 'Always speak the truth, think before you speak, and write it down afterwards.', 1253, 0), (468757, 'There''s nothing like a love for our children. I love being a papa, and that''s the truth.', 69378, 0), (468758, 'The calling of art is to extract us from our daily reality, to bring us to a hidden truth that''s difficult to access - to a level that''s not material but spiritual.', 21523, 0), (468759, 'I am a humble but very earnest seeker after truth.', 32, 0), (468760, 'It is a universal truth that the loss of liberty at home is to be charged to the provisions against danger, real or pretended, from abroad.', 2514, 0), (468761, 'How sweet the words of Truth, breathed from the lips of Love.', 11485, 0), (468762, 'I am aware that a philosopher''s ideas are not subject to the judgment of ordinary persons, because it is his endeavour to seek the truth in all things, to the extent permitted to human reason by God.', 4674, 0), (468763, 'God help us from those who believe that they are the sole possessors of truth. How we manage at times to agree willingly to become prisoners within our own minds and souls of beliefs and ideas on which we can never be flexible.', 68806, 0), (468764, 'To the scientist there is the joy in pursuing truth which nearly counteracts the depressing revelations of truth.', 1060, 0), (468765, 'Someone needs to tell the truth, but it shouldn''t be my job.', 70078, 0), (468766, 'The truth is in nature, and I shall prove it.', 19754, 0), (468767, 'The worst enemy of truth and freedom in our society is the compact majority.', 845, 0), (468768, 'We are either in the process of resisting God''s truth or in the process of being shaped and molded by his truth.', 67762, 0), (468769, 'Pain reaches the heart with electrical speed, but truth moves to the heart as slowly as a glacier.', 679, 0), (468770, 'The world is indeed a mixture of truth and make-believe. Discard the make-believe and take the truth.', 4269, 0), (468771, 'The challenge for a nonfiction writer is to achieve a poetic precision using the documents of truth but somehow to make people and places spring to life as if the reader was in their presence.', 20711, 0), (468772, 'There''s no point in saying anything but the truth.', 11891, 0), (468773, 'I had practiced with the team, and the first scheduled game was with the University of Missouri. They made it quite clear to the Army that they would not play a team with a black player on it. Instead of telling me the truth, the Army gave me leave to go home.', 38064, 0), (468774, 'The first step toward finding God, Who is Truth, is to discover the truth about myself: and if I have been in error, this first step to truth is the discovery of my error.', 123, 0), (468775, 'I hate newspapermen. They come into camp and pick up their camp rumors and print them as facts. I regard them as spies, which, in truth, they are.', 65193, 0), (468776, 'I have legs of iron, but to tell you the truth, they''re starting to rust and buckle a bit.', 49539, 0), (468777, 'There is another old poet whose name I do not now remember who said, ''Truth is the daughter of Time.''', 1012, 0), (468778, 'Any truth is better than indefinite doubt.', 764, 0), (468779, 'Truth exists only lies are invented. ', 30266, 0), (468780, 'I am bound to tell what I am told, but not in every case to believe it.', 1863, 0), (468781, 'Truth will rise above falsehood as oil above water.', 62284, 0), (468782, 'Truth can be costly, but in the end it never falls short of value for the price paid.', 3376, 0), (468783, 'I think this whole discussion about what is politically correct - sometimes you have to name the name. You can''t hide it. Politeness is good if it''s not hiding the truth.', 68963, 0), (468784, 'Never underestimate people. They do desire the cut of truth.', 3767, 0), (468785, 'When truth is discovered by someone else, it loses something of its attractiveness.', 2564, 0), (468786, 'How often have I said to you that when you have eliminated the impossible, whatever remains, however improbable, must be the truth?', 764, 0), (468787, 'In every truth, the beneficiaries of a system cannot be expected to destroy it.', 17593, 0), (468788, 'If the truth contradicts deeply held beliefs, that is too bad.', 66860, 0), (468789, 'Bad taste is simply saying the truth before it should be said.', 2237, 0), (468790, 'The truth is a snare: you cannot have it, without being caught. You cannot have the truth in such a way that you catch it, but only in such a way that it catches you.', 3131, 0), (468791, 'In truth, to know oneself seems to be the hardest of all things. Not only our eye, which observes external objects, does not use the sense of sight upon itself, but even our mind, which contemplates intently another''s sin, is slow in the recognition of its own defects.', 63774, 0), (468792, 'The truth cannot be deceptive, and one who sees it cannot be deceived.', 71936, 0), (468793, 'I used to say that the Constitution is not a living document. It''s dead, dead, dead. But I''ve gotten better. I no longer say that. The truth is that the Constitution is not one that morphs. It''s an enduring Constitution, not a changing Constitution. That is what I''ve meant when I''ve said that the Constitution is dead.', 21037, 0), (468794, 'A play is fiction - and fiction is fact distilled into truth.', 3231, 0), (468795, 'If I can get you to laugh with me, you like me better, which makes you more open to my ideas. And if I can persuade you to laugh at the particular point I make, by laughing at it you acknowledge its truth.', 8174, 0), (468796, 'A lie can be halfway round the world before the truth has got its boots on.', 74090, 0), (468797, 'The spirit of truth and the spirit of freedom - these are the pillars of society.', 845, 0), (468798, 'Proverbs are always platitudes until you have personally experienced the truth of them.', 1032, 0), (468799, 'For a creative writer possession of the ''truth'' is less important than emotional sincerity.', 521, 0), (468800, 'Pretty woman, I don''t believe you, you''re not the truth. No one could look as good as you, mercy.', 16454, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468801, 'Do not love leisure. Waste not a minute. Be bold. Realize the Truth, here and now!', 62960, 0), (468802, 'The price that one pays for refusing to act on the truth as one sees it, is to be led to believe untruth to avoid guilt.', 69533, 0), (468803, 'Be influenced by nothing but your clients'' interests. Tell them the truth.', 70582, 0), (468804, 'Love is not a mere impulse, it must contain truth, which is law.', 430, 0), (468805, 'Bigotry tries to keep truth safe in its hand with a grip that kills it.', 430, 0), (468806, 'To become properly acquainted with a truth, we must first have disbelieved it, and disputed against it.', 2510, 0), (468807, 'The man who cannot endure to have his errors and shortcomings brought to the surface and made known, but tries to hide them, is unfit to walk the highway of truth.', 2970, 0), (468808, 'Hinduism''s basic tenet is that many roads exist by which men have pursued and still pursue their quest for the truth and that none has universal validity.', 73331, 0), (468809, 'In seeking absolute truth we aim at the unattainable and must be content with broken portions.', 3668, 0), (468810, 'I detest jokes - when somebody tells me one, I feel my IQ dropping; the brain cells start to disappear. But something is funny when the person delivering the line doesn''t know it''s funny or doesn''t treat it as a joke. Maybe it comes from a place of truth, or it''s a sort of rage against society.', 148, 0), (468811, 'The least initial deviation from the truth is multiplied later a thousandfold.', 1116, 0), (468812, 'When you stretch the truth, watch out for the snapback.', 37846, 0), (468813, 'When the people who are responsible for our country ask you a direct question, I expect them to accept a direct answer, not to be blackballed because you are telling the truth.', 821, 0), (468814, 'The truth is that life is delicious, horrible, charming, frightful, sweet, bitter, and that is everything.', 348, 0), (468815, 'People will generally accept facts as truth only if the facts agree with what they already believe.', 1350, 0), (468816, 'All great truths begin as blasphemies.', 266, 0), (468817, 'My mother taught me that when you stand in the truth and someone tells a lie about you, don''t fight it.', 15469, 0), (468818, 'Gossip is called gossip because it''s not always the truth.', 58477, 0), (468819, 'Without accepting the fact that everything changes, we cannot find perfect composure. But unfortunately, although it is true, it is difficult for us to accept it. Because we cannot accept the truth of transience, we suffer.', 2504, 0), (468820, 'Son, always tell the truth. Then you''ll never have to remember what you said the last time.', 37565, 0), (468821, 'Don''t worry over what the newspapers say. I don''t. Why should anyone else? I told the truth to the newspaper correspondents - but when you tell the truth to them they are at sea.', 9728, 0), (468822, 'Truth, when not sought after, rarely comes to light.', 24754, 0), (468823, 'Whoever is detected in a shameful fraud is ever after not believed even if they speak the truth.', 62869, 0), (468824, 'All the religions of the world, while they may differ in other respects, unitedly proclaim that nothing lives in this world but Truth.', 32, 0), (468825, 'Truth, they say, is but too often in difficulties, but is never finally suppressed.', 14801, 0), (468826, 'If the sad truth be known, writers, being the misfits we are, probably ought not to belong to families in the first place. We simply are too self-interested, though we may excuse the flaw by calling it ''focused.''', 71167, 0), (468827, 'Some people have a difficult time facing truth and reality. They prefer to live in a make-believe world, pretending that certain things aren''t happening.', 1206, 0), (468828, 'Expressing truth is hard work.', 70991, 0), (468829, 'I have been known for some time as a person who speaks the truth and speaks it strongly. I have always called a liar a liar and a hypocrite a hypocrite.', 68797, 0), (468830, 'I am angry about the mammoth, out-of-control social welfare entitlement programs from Washington, D.C., that were supposed to solve our problems. The obvious truth is these impractical, politically motivated programs have irreparably damaged the fabric of our black society and community.', 71505, 0), (468831, 'The truth is, people don''t know me. When people don''t know you, they''re going to try to get to know you as quickly as possible, because you''re now taking the place of somebody that they love dearly, or somebody that they hate sincerely, and so they need to know who you are.', 1515, 0), (468832, 'The opportunity to declare a truth may come when we least expect it. Let us be prepared.', 327, 0), (468833, 'If you see voters as rational, you''ll be a terrible politician. People are not wired to be rational. Our brains simply evolved to keep us alive. Brains did not evolve to give us truth. Brains merely give us movies in our minds that keeps us sane and motivated. But none of it is rational or true, except maybe sometimes by coincidence.', 101, 0), (468834, 'I don''t want any yes-men around me. I want everybody to tell me the truth even if it costs them their job.', 31112, 0), (468835, 'What a word is truth. Slippery, tricky, unreliable. I tried in these books to tell the truth.', 1991, 0), (468836, 'Above all, I would teach him to tell the truth Truth-telling, I have found, is the key to responsible citizenship. The thousands of criminals I have seen in 40 years of law enforcement have had one thing in common: Every single one was a liar.', 72241, 0), (468837, 'Search for the truth. I tell you things and I always ask you to verify what I say. I told you yesterday that there was an attack and a retreat at Saddam''s airport.', 73061, 0), (468838, 'Accuracy of statement is one of the first elements of truth inaccuracy is a near kin to falsehood. ', 9316, 0), (468839, 'When distant and unfamiliar and complex things are communicated to great masses of people, the truth suffers a considerable and often a radical distortion. The complex is made over into the simple, the hypothetical into the dogmatic, and the relative into an absolute.', 3643, 0), (468840, 'Everything you add to the truth subtracts from the truth.', 2564, 0), (468841, 'The truth is balance. However the opposite of truth, which is unbalance, may not be a lie.', 4673, 0), (468842, 'A lie would have no sense unless the truth were felt dangerous.', 29457, 0), (468843, 'Every great discovery I ever made, I gambled that the truth was there, and then I acted in faith until I could prove its existence.', 74091, 0), (468844, 'You must have love as the core it takes courage to be willing to constantly tell the truth to each other and risk letting the relationship go. ', 71326, 0), (468845, 'When I saw corruption, I was forced to find truth on my own. I couldn''t swallow the hypocrisy.', 71751, 0), (468846, 'I don''t think Bosnia is ready for reconciliation, but I do think it is ready for truth.', 68875, 0), (468847, 'The inquiries of the jurist are in truth prosecuted much as inquiry in physic and physiology was prosecuted before observation had taken the place of assumption.', 73561, 0), (468848, 'It''s a great thriller or mystery, but on another level it''s a film about the fact that, if you only look at a person through one lens, or only believe what you''re told, you can often miss the truth that is staring you in the face.', 60302, 0), (468849, 'Everybody now admits that apartheid was wrong, and all I did was tell the people who wanted to know where I come from how we lived in South Africa. I just told the world the truth. And if my truth then becomes political, I can''t do anything about that.', 64289, 0), (468850, 'Let us be a little humble let us think that the truth may not perhaps be entirely with us. ', 8325, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468851, 'What I claim is to live to the full the contradiction of my time, which may well make sarcasm the condition of truth.', 909, 0), (468852, 'The Bible must be considered as the great source of all the truth by which men are to be guided in government as well as in all social transactions.', 10855, 0), (468853, 'Truth is not only violated by falsehood it may be equally outraged by silence. ', 4754, 0), (468854, 'Any fool can tell the truth, but it requires a man of some sense to know how to lie well.', 4111, 0), (468855, 'There is something wonderful in seeing a wrong-headed majority assailed by truth.', 4940, 0), (468856, 'What ever truth drops on it eventually grinds to a powder.', 71655, 0), (468857, 'Justice is truth in action.', 1827, 0), (468858, 'If any man seeks for greatness, let him forget greatness and ask for truth, and he will find both.', 2053, 0), (468859, 'Doubt is the incentive to truth and inquiry leads the way.', 32228, 0), (468860, 'Truth is strong, and sometime or other will prevail.', 16692, 0), (468861, 'Sure I think it is healthy to speak the truth, and be who you are, and be proud of that.', 68521, 0), (468862, 'Learn what is true in order to do what is right.', 63366, 0), (468863, 'I always felt that a scientist owes the world only one thing, and that is the truth as he sees it.', 66860, 0), (468864, 'It is an old maxim of mine that when you have excluded the impossible, whatever remains, however improbable, must be the truth.', 764, 0), (468865, 'One may sometimes tell a lie, but the grimace that accompanies it tells the truth.', 11, 0), (468866, 'The violinist must possess the poet''s gift of piercing the protective hide which grows on propagandists, stockbrokers and slave traders, to penetrate the deeper truth which lies within.', 11477, 0), (468867, 'Who never doubted, never half believed. Where doubt is, there truth is - it is her shadow.', 224, 0), (468868, 'Heresies are experiments in man''s unsatisfied search for truth.', 3173, 0), (468869, 'Truth emerges more readily from error than from confusion.', 1035, 0), (468870, 'It is more from carelessness about truth than from intentionally lying that there is so much falsehood in the world.', 2087, 0), (468871, 'Popular opinions, on subjects not palpable to sense, are often true, but seldom or never the whole truth.', 1880, 0), (468872, 'If you ever injected truth into politics you have no politics.', 1122, 0), (468873, 'The public will believe anything, so long as it is not founded on truth.', 1102, 0), (468874, 'Nothing leads the scientist so astray as a premature truth.', 3404, 0), (468875, 'Man''s mind is so formed that it is far more susceptible to falsehood than to truth.', 67390, 0), (468876, 'Defending the truth is not something one does out of a sense of duty or to allay guilt complexes, but is a reward in itself.', 477, 0), (468877, 'There is no original truth, only original error.', 3079, 0), (468878, 'Wisdom is found only in truth.', 282, 0), (468879, 'A petty reason perhaps why novelists more and more try to keep a distance from journalists is that novelists are trying to write the truth and journalists are trying to write fiction.', 429, 0), (468880, 'I never gave anybody hell! I just told the truth and they thought it was hell.', 16121, 0), (468881, 'Lawyers enjoy a little mystery, you know. Why, if everybody came forward and told the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth straight out, we should all retire to the workhouse.', 3165, 0), (468882, 'As Commander in Chief of the United States Military, I will never send our sons and daughters and our brothers and sisters to die in a foreign land without telling the truth about why they''re going there.', 17529, 0), (468883, 'We should not be so taken up in the search for truth, as to neglect the needful duties of active life; for it is only action that gives a true value and commendation to virtue.', 1306, 0), (468884, 'The object of oratory alone in not truth, but persuasion.', 13860, 0), (468885, 'Not when truth is dirty, but when it is shallow, does the enlightened man dislike to wade into its waters.', 11, 0), (468886, 'Traditional scientific method has always been at the very best, 20 - 20 hindsight. It''s good for seeing where you''ve been. It''s good for testing the truth of what you think you know, but it can''t tell you where you ought to go.', 1742, 0), (468887, 'Truth, which is important to a scholar, has got to be concrete. And there is nothing more concrete than dealing with babies, burps and bottles, frogs and mud.', 3797, 0), (468888, 'The audience is the best judge of anything. They cannot be lied to. Truth brings them closer. A moment that lags - they''re gonna cough.', 3756, 0), (468889, 'We occasionally stumble over the truth but most of us pick ourselves up and hurry off as if nothing had happened.', 3621, 0), (468890, 'He who sees the truth, let him proclaim it, without asking who is for it or who is against it.', 40782, 0), (468891, 'For truth is always strange stranger than fiction. ', 62558, 0), (468892, 'The American people need to know the truth. The American people need to see the truth. In a democracy, letting the people know the truth is the essence of what it means to be free.', 71482, 0), (468893, 'Every scientific truth goes through three states: first, people say it conflicts with the Bible; next, they say it has been discovered before; lastly, they say they always believed it.', 23130, 0), (468894, 'Grow your tree of falsehood from a small grain of truth. Do not follow those who lie in contempt of reality. Let your lie be even more logical than the truth itself, so the weary travelers may find repose.', 73067, 0), (468895, 'In truth, the only restrictions on our capacity to astonish ourselves and each other are imposed by our own minds.', 67510, 0), (468896, 'We must never throw away a bushel of truth because it happens to contain a few grains of chaff.', 74092, 0), (468897, 'I would rather the man who presents something for my consideration subject me to a zephyr of truth and a gentle breeze of responsibility rather than blow me down with a curtain of hot wind.', 18162, 0), (468898, 'But that citizen''s perception was also at one with the truth in recognizing that the very brutality of the means by which the IRA were pursuing change was destructive of the trust upon which new possibilities would have to be based.', 1422, 0), (468899, 'In fact, in lyric poetry, truthfulness becomes recognizable as a ring of truth within the medium itself.', 1422, 0), (468900, 'The modern composer builds upon the foundation of truth.', 71691, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468901, 'To begin with myself, then, the utterances of men concerning me will differ widely, since in passing judgment almost every one is influenced not so much by truth as by preference, and good and evil report alike know no bounds.', 66050, 0), (468902, 'There is in the end no remedy but truth. It is the one course that cannot be evil.', 3376, 0), (468903, 'It took a deadly illness to put me eye to eye with that truth, but it is a truth that the country, caught up in its ruthless ambitions and moral decay, can learn on my dime.', 45226, 0), (468904, 'The truth of the matter was that I made myself disappear. I never liked being a Judge, so I just decided to start over. Sorry to inconvenience anyone.', 74093, 0), (468905, 'Until we have a better relationship between private performance and the public truth, as was demonstrated with Watergate, we as the public are absolutely right to remain suspicious, contemptuous even, of the secrecy and the misinformation which is the digest of our news.', 5956, 0), (468906, 'What I''m dealing with is so vast and great that it can''t be called the truth. It''s above the truth.', 42348, 0), (468907, 'If you tell the truth about how you''re feeling, it becomes funny.', 51334, 0), (468908, 'It would be difficult to discover the truth about the universe if we refused to consider anything that might be true.', 3026, 0), (468909, 'I want a language that speaks the truth.', 16129, 0), (468910, 'When a truth is necessary, the reason for it can be found by analysis, that is, by resolving it into simpler ideas and truths until the primary ones are reached.', 70838, 0), (468911, 'When a man fails to see the truth of certain generally accepted views, there is no law compelling him to provoke animosity by announcing his dissent.', 41950, 0), (468912, 'The truth is that from birth on we are, to one extent or another, a fairly sensual species.', 74094, 0), (468913, 'Unemployment is sky-rocketing; deflation is in our future for the first time since the Great Depression. I don''t care whose fault it is, it''s the truth.', 12435, 0), (468914, 'This Divine truth flows into heaven from the Lord from His Divine love.', 14267, 0), (468915, 'I was a very good baseball and football player, but my father always told me I was much more interested in how I looked playing baseball or football than in actually playing. There''s great truth in that.', 18212, 0), (468916, 'On the stage, you have to find truth, even if you have to lose the audience.', 74095, 0), (468917, 'I am afraid the Spanish American has not always a very strict regard for truth.', 74096, 0), (468918, 'I always try to improve, to find new ways of expressing myself, to keep looking for truth and originality.', 74097, 0), (468919, 'My assignment is what every writer''s assignment is: tell the truth of his own time.', 69089, 0), (468920, 'I think that the truth is a really stern taskmistress.', 1288, 0), (468921, 'A gift of truth is the gift of love.', 21153, 0), (468922, 'I believe certain members of the U.S. Congress have aided in the oppression and diversion of critical information that could have revealed a fullness of truth long ago.', 74098, 0), (468923, 'A remark generally hurts in proportion to its truth.', 1122, 0), (468924, 'The truth may be out there, but lies are inside your head.', 195, 0), (468925, 'Man approaches the unattainable truth through a succession of errors.', 1032, 0), (468926, 'Beyond a doubt truth bears the same relation to falsehood as light to darkness.', 1386, 0), (468927, 'Books and all forms of writing are terror to those who wish to suppress the truth.', 6613, 0), (468928, 'I speak the truth not so much as I would, but as much as I dare, and I dare a little more as I grow older.', 663, 0), (468929, 'The greatest friend of truth is Time, her greatest enemy is Prejudice, and her constant companion is Humility.', 432, 0), (468930, 'Poetry a criticism of life under the conditions fixed for such a criticism by the laws of poetic truth and poetic beauty. ', 460, 0), (468931, 'People do think that if they avoid the truth, it might change to something better before they have to hear it.', 9758, 0), (468932, 'Truth is not exciting enough to those who depend on the characters and lives of their neighbors for all their amusement.', 66540, 0), (468933, 'The world is... the natural setting of, and field for, all my thoughts and all my explicit perceptions. Truth does not inhabit only the inner man, or more accurately, there is no inner man, man is in the world, and only in the world does he know himself.', 2801, 0), (468934, 'In morals, truth is but little prized when it is a mere sentiment, and only attains its full value when realized in the world as fact.', 21120, 0), (468935, 'Some minds remain open long enough for the truth not only to enter but to pass on through by way of a ready exit without pausing anywhere along the route.', 63752, 0), (468936, 'I put forward formless and unresolved notions, as do those who publish doubtful questions to debate in the schools, not to establish the truth but to seek it.', 663, 0), (468937, 'It is good to express a thing twice right at the outset and so to give it a right foot and also a left one. Truth can surely stand on one leg, but with two it will be able to walk and get around.', 11, 0), (468938, 'Truth is the silliest thing under the sun. Try to get a living by the Truth and go to the Soup Societies. Heavens! Let any clergyman try to preach the Truth from its very stronghold, the pulpit, and they would ride him out of his church on his own pulpit bannister.', 2584, 0), (468939, 'The tendency of modern scientific teaching is to neglect the great books, to lay far too much stress upon relatively unimportant modern work, and to present masses of detail of doubtful truth and questionable weight in such a way as to obscure principles.', 74099, 0), (468940, 'Justice and truth are too such subtle points that our tools are too blunt to touch them accurately.', 144, 0), (468941, 'Friendless. Having no favors to bestow. Destitute of fortune. Addicted to utterance of truth and common sense.', 224, 0), (468942, 'Truth titillates the imagination far less than fiction.', 2459, 0), (468943, 'A gaffe is when a politician tells the truth.', 67237, 0), (468944, 'Fiction is obliged to stick to possibilities. Truth isn''t.', 286, 0), (468945, 'Truth is the property of no individual but is the treasure of all men.', 760, 0), (468946, 'All credibility, all good conscience, all evidence of truth come only from the senses.', 11, 0), (468947, 'Power is not sufficient evidence of truth.', 2087, 0), (468948, 'I am very fond of truth, but not at all of martyrdom.', 808, 0), (468949, 'A taste for truth at any cost is a passion which spares nothing.', 532, 0), (468950, 'A good novel tells us the truth about its hero but a bad novel tells us the truth about its author. ', 67663, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (468951, 'Half a truth is better than no politics.', 67663, 0), (468952, 'In matters of truth the fact that you don''t want to publish something is, nine times out of ten, a proof that you ought to publish it.', 67663, 0), (468953, 'The Bible may be the truth, but it is not the whole truth and nothing but the truth.', 4111, 0), (468954, 'An unexciting truth may be eclipsed by a thrilling lie.', 1032, 0), (468955, 'An honest man speaks the truth, though it may give offence; a vain man, in order that it may.', 8948, 0), (468956, 'Truth is what works.', 1782, 0), (468957, 'Live truth instead of professing it.', 4, 0), (468958, 'Richard Nixon is a no good, lying bastard. He can lie out of both sides of his mouth at the same time, and if he ever caught himself telling the truth, he''d lie just to keep his hand in.', 16121, 0), (468959, 'The words of truth are simple.', 1882, 0), (468960, 'Truth is often the favorite tool of those who deceive.', 24882, 0), (468961, 'The essence of humanity''s spiritual dilemma is that we evolved genetically to accept one truth and discovered another. Is there a way to erase the dilemma, to resolve the contradictions between the transcendentalist and the empiricist world views?', 44747, 0), (468962, 'Veiling truth in mystery.', 1462, 0), (468963, 'Whatever has happened in my quest for innovation has been part of my quest for immaculate reality.', 1110, 0), (468964, 'The logic of the world is prior to all truth and falsehood.', 1163, 0), (468965, 'Light is the symbol of truth.', 1247, 0), (468966, 'Truth forever on the scaffold, wrong forever on the throne.', 1247, 0), (468967, 'Humility is truth.', 67390, 0), (468968, 'For truth has such a face and such a mien, as to be loved needs only to be seen.', 8695, 0), (468969, 'Only in men''s imagination does every truth find an effective and undeniable existence. Imagination, not invention, is the supreme master of art as of life.', 1241, 0), (468970, 'Truth of a modest sort I can promise you, and also sincerity. That complete, praiseworthy sincerity which, while it delivers one into the hands of one''s enemies, is as likely as not to embroil one with one''s friends.', 1241, 0), (468971, 'Truth always originates in a minority of one, and every custom begins as a broken precedent.', 1167, 0), (468972, 'Truth is not a matter of personal viewpoint.', 1508, 0), (468973, 'If the individual, or heretic, gets hold of some essential truth, or sees some error in the system being practiced, he commits so many marginal errors himself that he is worn out before he can establish his point.', 8630, 0), (468974, 'Not that I regret saying what I believed to be the truth, but I regret anything that I might have written or spoken that could have been used in a way to help to foster that atmosphere out of which came the loss of life of Brother Malcolm.', 51994, 0), (468975, 'Truth makes on the ocean of nature no one track of light; every eye, looking on, finds its own.', 62596, 0), (468976, 'Infinite love is the only truth. Everything else is illusion.', 21153, 0), (468977, 'The pursuit of truth will set you free even if you never catch up with it. ', 2052, 0), (468978, 'While we are examining into everything we sometimes find truth where we least expected it.', 63010, 0), (468979, 'What is truth? Truth doesn''t really exist. Who is going to judge whether my experience of an incident is more valid than yours? No one can be trusted to be the judge of that.', 26735, 0), (468980, 'No one ever tells us the truth, even those we love.', 55096, 0), (468981, 'Nobody speaks the truth when there is something they must have.', 6481, 0), (468982, 'I will tell the truth wherever I please.', 1505, 0), (468983, 'I left in love, in laughter, and in truth, and wherever truth, love and laughter abide, I am there in spirit.', 544, 0), (468984, 'There are certain persons for whom pure Truth is a poison.', 10019, 0), (468985, 'Unless one always speaks the truth, one cannot find God Who is the soul of truth.', 4269, 0), (468986, 'For scholarship - if it is to be scholarship - requires, in addition to liberty, that the truth take precedence over all sectarian interests, including self-interest.', 70915, 0), (468987, 'Truth sits upon the lips of dying men.', 460, 0), (468988, 'The first reaction to truth is hatred.', 3445, 0), (468989, 'The honest truth is that if this government were to propose the massacre of the first-born, it would still have no difficulty in getting it through the Commons.', 70312, 0), (468990, 'No one should ever say that it was my ignorance if I did or showed forth anything however small according to God''s good pleasure; but let this be your conclusion and let it so be thought, that - as is the perfect truth - it was the gift of God.', 66870, 0), (468991, 'The truth is overrated.', 74100, 0), (468992, 'I preach there are all kinds of truth, your truth and somebody else''s. But behind all of them there is only one truth and that is that there''s no truth.', 931, 0), (468993, 'Justice is rather the activity of truth, than a virtue in itself. Truth tells us what is due to others, and justice renders that due. Injustice is acting a lie.', 1081, 0), (468994, 'My longing for truth was a single prayer.', 73510, 0), (468995, 'Truth comes out in wine.', 3240, 0), (468996, 'Truth disappears with the telling of it.', 6034, 0), (468997, 'Falsehood is cowardice, the truth courage.', 32228, 0), (468998, 'Claiming that you have got the truth wrapped up does breed violence and intolerance.', 74101, 0), (468999, 'Truth is stranger than fiction fiction has to make sense. ', 1898, 0), (469000, 'If we were to abandon concern for what is true, what is false, and what remains indeterminate, the world would be totally chaotic. Even those who deny the importance of truth, on the one hand, are quick to jump on anyone who is caught lying.', 11453, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469001, 'To tell you the truth, in my work, love is always in opposition to the elements. It creates dilemmas. It brings in suffering. We can''t live with it, and we can''t live without it. You''ll rarely find a happy ending in my work.', 38439, 0), (469002, 'I think I''m telling the truth. I sat by Ray Perkins at the Hall of Fame dinner in New York, and at that time he didn''t know he was our coach and I didn''t either.', 74102, 0), (469003, 'Not so the scientist. The very essence of his life is the service of truth.', 67361, 0), (469004, 'Human love has little regard for the truth. It makes the truth relative, since nothing, not even the truth, must come between it and the beloved person.', 741, 0), (469005, 'In the last few years, the very idea of telling the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth is dredged up only as a final resort when the alternative options of deception, threat and bribery have all been exhausted.', 74103, 0), (469006, 'Everybody in America is soft, and hates conflict. The cure for this, both in politics and social life, is the same - hardihood. Give them raw truth.', 62700, 0), (469007, 'Slogans which deafened us so that we could not hear the truth.', 16198, 0), (469008, 'Because you''re not what I would have you be, I blind myself to who, in truth, you are.', 962, 0), (469009, 'Now the truth of the matter is that there are a lot of things people don''t understand. Take the Einstein theory. Take taxes. Take love. Do you understand them? Neither do I. But they exist. They happen.', 7843, 0), (469010, 'In this play we''re dealing with relative truths - who''s lying, who''s telling the truth. But underneath that, Ed and I have hit this deeper level of intimacy between old friends that comes out in the play.', 73051, 0), (469011, 'And the sad truth is that nobody wants me to write comedy. The Exorcist not only ended that career, it expunged all memory of its existence.', 7229, 0), (469012, 'Mind and spirit together make up that which separates us from the rest of the animal world, that which enables a man to know the truth and that which enables him to die for the truth.', 749, 0), (469013, 'The Spirit is Love expressed towards man as redeeming love, and the Spirit is truth, and the Spirit is the Holy Spirit. Redemption is inconceivable without truth and holiness.', 74104, 0), (469014, 'The idealists dream and the dream is told, and the practical men listen and ponder and bring back the truth and apply it to human life, and progress and growth and higher human ideals come into being and so the world moves ever on.', 66155, 0), (469015, 'Accuracy of language is one of the bulwarks of truth.', 63997, 0), (469016, 'Never ever doubt in magic. The purest honest thoughts come from children, ask any child if they believe in magic and they will tell you the truth.', 74105, 0), (469017, 'The intuition of free will gives us the truth.', 56184, 0), (469018, 'The absolute truth is the thing that makes people laugh.', 59036, 0), (469019, 'The antiquity and general acceptance of an opinion is not assurance of its truth.', 73113, 0), (469020, 'Any necessary truth, whether a priori or a posteriori, could not have turned out otherwise.', 74106, 0), (469021, 'Every emancipation has in it the seeds of a new slavery, and every truth easily becomes a lie.', 17525, 0), (469022, 'The truth cannot be asserted without denouncing the falsehood.', 4323, 0), (469023, 'I am a fighter. I believe in that which is right, and the truth is, I have been the Lone Ranger for the past thirty years and I will not give up the fight. I love my public and I''ll fight for you. I''ll continue to make personal appearances for my thousands of fans.', 74107, 0), (469024, 'The ultimate aim of the human mind, in all its efforts, is to become acquainted with Truth.', 73647, 0), (469025, 'Literature boils with the madcap careers of writers brought to the edge by the demands of living on their nerves, wringing out their memories and their nightmares to extract meaning, truth, beauty.', 74108, 0), (469026, 'I was not out to paint beautiful pictures even painting good pictures was not important to me. I wanted only to help the truth burst forth. ', 2806, 0), (469027, 'He who is not courageous enough to take risks will accomplish nothing in life.', 1751, 0), (469028, 'Mistakes are always forgivable, if one has the courage to admit them.', 510, 0), (469029, 'We don''t develop courage by being happy every day. We develop it by surviving difficult times and challenging adversity.', 28913, 0), (469030, 'If you have no confidence in self, you are twice defeated in the race of life.', 1353, 0), (469031, 'Courage, sacrifice, determination, commitment, toughness, heart, talent, guts. That''s what little girls are made of.', 10127, 0), (469032, 'Courage is what it takes to stand up and speak courage is also what it takes to sit down and listen. ', 3621, 0), (469033, 'Efforts and courage are not enough without purpose and direction.', 1680, 0), (469034, 'The greatest test of courage on earth is to bear defeat without losing heart.', 67335, 0), (469035, 'Courage is fire, and bullying is smoke.', 1827, 0), (469036, 'Wisdom, compassion, and courage are the three universally recognized moral qualities of men.', 819, 0), (469037, 'Jump, and you will find out how to unfold your wings as you fall.', 567, 0), (469038, 'One isn''t necessarily born with courage, but one is born with potential. Without courage, we cannot practice any other virtue with consistency. We can''t be kind, true, merciful, generous, or honest.', 74, 0), (469039, 'The opposite for courage is not cowardice, it is conformity. Even a dead fish can go with the flow.', 62962, 0), (469040, 'I think we all have empathy. We may not have enough courage to display it.', 74, 0), (469041, 'From caring comes courage.', 15, 0), (469042, 'If human beings had genuine courage, they''d wear their costumes every day of the year, not just on Halloween.', 1002, 0), (469043, 'Courage is not simply one of the virtues, but the form of every virtue at the testing point.', 26, 0), (469044, 'Courage is grace under pressure.', 110, 0), (469045, 'Courage, above all things, is the first quality of a warrior.', 2677, 0), (469046, 'You will never do anything in this world without courage. It is the greatest quality of the mind next to honor.', 1116, 0), (469047, 'Don''t Make Assumptions. Find the courage to ask questions and to express what you really want. Communicate with others as clearly as you can to avoid misunderstandings, sadness and drama. With just this one agreement, you can completely transform your life.', 67703, 0), (469048, 'He is a man of courage who does not run away, but remains at his post and fights against the enemy.', 1595, 0), (469049, 'Creativity takes courage.', 4050, 0), (469050, 'As a former NFL player, I am one American who will have nothing to do with any NFL Team that cannot find the corporate courage to stand for the millions of courageous past great Americans whose sacrifice gave meaning to our flag and national anthem and to the millions upon millions who still dream to come to its free shores.', 70728, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469051, 'On great teams - the kind where people trust each other, engage in open conflict, and then commit to decisions - team members have the courage and confidence to confront one another when they see something that isn''t serving the team.', 17487, 0), (469052, 'Success is not measured by what you accomplish, but by the opposition you have encountered, and the courage with which you have maintained the struggle against overwhelming odds.', 4025, 0), (469053, 'Courage is contagious. When a brave man takes a stand, the spines of others are often stiffened.', 4008, 0), (469054, 'The principles of living greatly include the capacity to face trouble with courage, disappointment with cheerfulness, and trial with humility.', 327, 0), (469055, 'I know what it is to feel unloved, to want revenge, to make mistakes, to suffer disappointment, yet also to find the courage to go forward in life.', 3159, 0), (469056, 'Courtesy is as much a mark of a gentleman as courage.', 1674, 0), (469057, 'Let us not pray to be sheltered from dangers but to be fearless when facing them.', 430, 0), (469058, 'Competing at the highest level is not about winning. It''s about preparation, courage, understanding and nurturing your people, and heart. Winning is the result.', 63097, 0), (469059, 'I believe that my worth is not measured by what I do, by the honors that are bestowed upon me, or by material wealth that I might obtain. Instead, I am measured by the courage I show while standing for my beliefs, by the dedication I exhibit to ensure my word is good, and the resolve I undertake to establish my actions and deeds as honorable.', 70728, 0), (469060, 'People say to me all the time, ''You have no fear.'' I tell them, ''No, that''s not true. I''m scared all the time. You have to have fear in order to have courage. I''m a courageous person because I''m a scared person.''', 25405, 0), (469061, 'The greatest obstacle to being heroic is the doubt whether one may not be going to prove one''s self a fool; the truest heroism is to resist the doubt; and the profoundest wisdom, to know when it ought to be resisted, and when it be obeyed.', 650, 0), (469062, 'There are no easy answers, but there are simple answers. We must have the courage to do what we know is morally right.', 1727, 0), (469063, 'One man with courage is a majority.', 1207, 0), (469064, 'Soldiers, when committed to a task, can''t compromise. It''s unrelenting devotion to the standards of duty and courage, absolute loyalty to others, not letting the task go until it''s been done.', 16118, 0), (469065, 'With courage and character, American soldiers continue to put themselves on the line to defend our freedom, and so many have paid the ultimate sacrifice.', 72463, 0), (469066, 'It is my deepest belief that only by giving our lives do we find life. I am convinced that the truest act of courage, the strongest act of manliness is to sacrifice ourselves for others in a totally non-violent struggle for justice.', 28772, 0), (469067, 'Muhammad Ali struck us in the middle of America''s darkest night, in the heart of its most threatening gathering storm. His power toppled the mightiest of foes, and his intense light shined on America, and we were able to see clearly injustice, inequality, poverty, pride, self realization, courage, laughter, love, joy and religious freedom for all.', 22849, 0), (469068, 'Valor is stability, not of legs and arms, but of courage and the soul.', 663, 0), (469069, 'How few there are who have courage enough to own their faults, or resolution enough to mend them.', 1077, 0), (469070, 'Character contributes to beauty. It fortifies a woman as her youth fades. A mode of conduct, a standard of courage, discipline, fortitude, and integrity can do a great deal to make a woman beautiful.', 18672, 0), (469071, 'In the Soviet army it takes more courage to retreat than advance.', 11422, 0), (469072, 'We''ve begun to raise daughters more like sons... but few have the courage to raise our sons more like our daughters.', 1739, 0), (469073, 'Faced with what is right, to leave it undone shows a lack of courage.', 819, 0), (469074, 'I think we judge talent wrong. What do we see as talent? I think I have made the same mistake myself. We judge talent by people''s ability to strike a cricket ball. The sweetness, the timing. That''s the only thing we see as talent. Things like determination, courage, discipline, temperament, these are also talent.', 69228, 0), (469075, 'It is courage, courage, courage, that raises the blood of life to crimson splendor. Live bravely and present a brave front to adversity.', 2542, 0), (469076, 'A man of courage never needs weapons, but he may need bail.', 13474, 0), (469077, 'Make-up is the last thing to enhance your beauty, but it''s very important because it builds up your self-confidence and gives you more courage.', 71889, 0), (469078, 'He who is brave is free.', 65434, 0), (469079, 'The opposite of courage in our society is not cowardice, it is conformity.', 2467, 0), (469080, 'You have setbacks in your life, and adversity. You can be discouraged about it or have courage to get through it and be better.', 74109, 0), (469081, 'Happy are those who dare courageously to defend what they love.', 782, 0), (469082, 'Optimism is essential to achievement and it is also the foundation of courage and true progress.', 62715, 0), (469083, 'You have to develop ways so that you can take up for yourself, and then you take up for someone else. And so sooner or later, you have enough courage to really stand up for the human race and say, ''I''m a representative.''', 74, 0), (469084, 'Australia is a nation of compassion. Courage and compassion. And the third of these great values: resilience.', 67684, 0), (469085, 'To create one''s world in any of the arts takes courage.', 1944, 0), (469086, 'The strangest, most generous, and proudest of all virtues is true courage.', 663, 0), (469087, 'Real nobility is based on scorn, courage, and profound indifference.', 532, 0), (469088, 'The first virtue in a soldier is endurance of fatigue courage is only the second virtue. ', 1702, 0), (469089, 'Either you decide to stay in the shallow end of the pool or you go out in the ocean.', 7193, 0), (469090, 'He who has courage and faith will never perish in misery!', 986, 0), (469091, 'Boldness be my friend.', 13, 0), (469092, 'Presumption should never make us neglect that which appears easy to us, nor despair make us lose courage at the sight of difficulties.', 67374, 0), (469093, 'True courage is like a kite a contrary wind raises it higher. ', 74110, 0), (469094, 'Untutored courage is useless in the face of educated bullets.', 57896, 0), (469095, 'Any intelligent fool can make things bigger and more complex... It takes a touch of genius - and a lot of courage to move in the opposite direction.', 66889, 0), (469096, 'Bravery is being the only one who knows you''re afraid.', 62728, 0), (469097, 'We all live in the same house, we all must be part of the effort to hold down our little house. When you see something that is not right, not fair, not just... do something about it. Say something. Have the courage. Have the backbone. Get in the way. Walk with the wind. It''s all going to work out.', 36727, 0), (469098, 'People with courage and character always seem sinister to the rest.', 305, 0), (469099, 'Courage is a kind of salvation.', 51, 0), (469100, 'Physical bravery is an animal instinct moral bravery is much higher and truer courage. ', 24952, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469101, 'The courage of life is often a less dramatic spectacle than the courage of a final moment but it is no less a magnificent mixture of triumph and tragedy. ', 1680, 0), (469102, 'The test of courage comes when we are in the minority. The test of tolerance comes when we are in the majority.', 29211, 0), (469103, 'Killing yourself is a major commitment, it takes a kind of courage. Most people just lead lives of cowardly desperation. It''s kinda half suicide where you just dull yourself with substances.', 70733, 0), (469104, 'The British were indeed very far superior to the Americans in every respect necessary to military operations, except the revivified courage and resolution, the result of sudden success after despair.', 70796, 0), (469105, 'If you could get up the courage to begin, you have the courage to succeed.', 880, 0), (469106, 'Do not lose courage in considering your own imperfections.', 63291, 0), (469107, 'There has to be this pioneer, the individual who has the courage, the ambition to overcome the obstacles that always develop when one tries to do something worthwhile, especially when it is new and different.', 74111, 0), (469108, 'The difficult thing is that vulnerability is the first thing I look for in you and the last thing I''m willing to show you. In you, it''s courage and daring. In me, it''s weakness.', 247, 0), (469109, 'Anyone can support a team that is winning - it takes no courage. But to stand behind a team to defend a team when it is down and really needs you, that takes a lot of courage.', 66902, 0), (469110, 'Courage - a perfect sensibility of the measure of danger, and a mental willingness to endure it.', 65193, 0), (469111, 'Morality may consist solely in the courage of making a choice.', 63065, 0), (469112, 'Love and peace of mind do protect us. They allow us to overcome the problems that life hands us. They teach us to survive... to live now... to have the courage to confront each day.', 64551, 0), (469113, 'If you want to lose 40 pounds, you order salad instead of fries. If you want to be a better friend, you take the phone call instead of screening it. If you want to write a novel, you sit down and write a single paragraph. It''s scary to make major changes, but we usually have enough courage to take the next right step.', 37774, 0), (469114, 'True courage is not the brutal force of vulgar heroes, but the firm resolve of virtue and reason.', 2606, 0), (469115, 'Earth teach me to forget myself as melted snow forgets its life. Earth teach me resignation as the leaves which die in the fall. Earth teach me courage as the tree which stands all alone. Earth teach me regeneration as the seed which rises in the spring.', 44476, 0), (469116, 'Courage means to keep working a relationship, to continue seeking solutions to difficult problems, and to stay focused during stressful periods.', 1391, 0), (469117, 'You can''t forgive without loving. And I don''t mean sentimentality. I don''t mean mush. I mean having enough courage to stand up and say, ''I forgive. I''m finished with it.''', 74, 0), (469118, 'Courage is rightly esteemed the first of human qualities... because it is the quality which guarantees all others.', 3621, 0), (469119, 'Moral courage is higher and a rarer virtue than physical courage.', 74112, 0), (469120, 'Have the courage to face a difficulty lest it kick you harder than you bargain for.', 63596, 0), (469121, 'The weak in courage is strong in cunning.', 221, 0), (469122, 'To show that a comedian on stage in India talking about sanitation or in South Africa talking about HIV and AIDS awareness, if you follow the joke into their lives, you can see that, like, oh, these things aren''t just contrived in joke books. This is real life. I think the best comedians have that bravery and courage to say, Oh, this is what it is.', 68420, 0), (469123, 'The principal act of courage is to endure and withstand dangers doggedly rather than to attack them.', 1539, 0), (469124, 'True courage is being afraid, and going ahead and doing your job anyhow, that''s what courage is.', 4137, 0), (469125, 'Courage in danger is half the battle.', 62134, 0), (469126, 'We''ve let the blade of our innocence dull over time, and it''s only in innocence that you find any kind of magic, any kind of courage.', 3185, 0), (469127, 'I''m sick of not having the courage to be an absolute nobody.', 268, 0), (469128, 'Courage is never to let your actions be influenced by your fears.', 14934, 0), (469129, 'The courage to be is the courage to accept oneself, in spite of being unacceptable.', 2750, 0), (469130, 'Never be discouraged. If I were sunk in the lowest pits of Nova Scotia, with the Rocky Mountains piled on me, I would hang on, exercise faith, and keep up good courage, and I would come out on top.', 3554, 0), (469131, 'You must study to be frank with the world: Frankness is the child of honesty and courage.', 1924, 0), (469132, 'Believers, look up - take courage. The angels are nearer than you think.', 4008, 0), (469133, 'Part of courage is simple consistency.', 17507, 0), (469134, 'When you put on clothes that are fighting against something, you can feel your courage grow. Clothing can set you free.', 69764, 0), (469135, 'Each person has inside a basic decency and goodness. If he listens to it and acts on it, he is giving a great deal of what it is the world needs most. It is not complicated but it takes courage. It takes courage for a person to listen to his own goodness and act on it.', 19733, 0), (469136, 'Courage is willingness to take the risk once you know the odds. Optimistic overconfidence means you are taking the risk because you don''t know the odds. It''s a big difference.', 6017, 0), (469137, 'A nation which has forgotten the quality of courage which in the past has been brought to public life is not as likely to insist upon or regard that quality in its chosen leaders today - and in fact we have forgotten.', 1680, 0), (469138, 'Optimism is the foundation of courage.', 62715, 0), (469139, 'Today we affirm a new commitment to live out our nation''s promise through civility, courage, compassion and character.', 2358, 0), (469140, 'Unless a reviewer has the courage to give you unqualified praise, I say ignore the bastard.', 1070, 0), (469141, 'Peace is a fragile thing. It takes courage to secure it. It takes wisdom to maintain it.', 71483, 0), (469142, 'The man who has the courage of his platitudes is always a successful man.', 34486, 0), (469143, 'Courage and willingness to just go for it, whether it is a conversation or a spontaneous trip or trying new things that are scary - it is a really attractive quality.', 21687, 0), (469144, 'Buddhist practices offer a way of saying, ''Hey, come back over here, reconnect.'' The only way that you''ll actually wake up and have some freedom is if you have the capacity and courage to stay with the vulnerability and the discomfort.', 14256, 0), (469145, 'I can tell you character traits I admire and work to develop in myself - perseverance, self-discipline, courage to stand up for what is right even when it is against one''s friends or one''s self.', 74113, 0), (469146, 'The only thing is, people have to develop courage. It is most important of all the virtues. Because without courage, you can''t practice any other virtues consistently.', 74, 0), (469147, 'My mother always taught us that if people don''t agree with you, the important thing is to listen to them. But if you''ve listened to them carefully and you still think that you''re right, then you must have the courage of your convictions.', 2086, 0), (469148, 'Most people talk; we do things. They plan; we achieve. They hesitate; we move ahead. We are living proof that when human beings have the courage and commitment to transform a dream into reality, there is nothing that can stop them.', 26541, 0), (469149, 'I would like to tell the young men and women before me not to lose hope 