INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469151, 'There are pretenders to piety as well as to courage.', 1695, 0), (469152, 'Guilt is just as powerful, but its influence is positive, while shame''s is destructive. Shame erodes our courage and fuels disengagement.', 247, 0), (469153, 'For thousands of years, human beings have been obsessed with beauty, truth, love, honor, altruism, courage, social relationships, art, and God. They all go together as subjective experiences, and it''s a straw man to set God up as the delusion. If he is, then so is truth itself or beauty itself.', 1194, 0), (469154, 'I''ve always been independent. I''ve always had courage. But I didn''t always own my diabetes.', 1180, 0), (469155, 'Fearlessness is not only possible, it is the ultimate joy. When you touch nonfear, you are free.', 394, 0), (469156, 'To see what is right and not to do it is want of courage, or of principle.', 819, 0), (469157, 'Honest conviction is my courage the Constitution is my guide. ', 74114, 0), (469158, 'We learned to be patient observers like the owl. We learned cleverness from the crow, and courage from the jay, who will attack an owl ten times its size to drive it off its territory. But above all of them ranked the chickadee because of its indomitable spirit.', 71148, 0), (469159, 'My sword I give to him that shall succeed me in my pilgrimage, and my courage and skill to him that can get it.', 1778, 0), (469160, 'If the Christian is a restorationist, a legalist, if he wants everything clear and safe, then he will find nothing. Tradition and memory of the past must help us to have the courage to open up new areas to God.', 6248, 0), (469161, 'Only choices made in love are compassionate. There are no exceptions. Do you have the courage to act with an empowered heart without attachment to the outcome? If not, you have no ability to give or experience compassion. That is the shocking truth.', 21209, 0), (469162, 'Life is to be entered upon with courage.', 4021, 0), (469163, 'Courage is being afraid but going on anyhow.', 12782, 0), (469164, 'I know of no higher fortitude than stubborness in the face of overwhelming odds.', 31146, 0), (469165, 'It requires more courage to suffer than to die.', 1702, 0), (469166, 'I have a lot of things to prove to myself. One is that I can live my life fearlessly.', 588, 0), (469167, 'A great deal of talent is lost to the world for want of a little courage. Every day sends to their graves obscure men whose timidity prevented them from making a first effort.', 9771, 0), (469168, 'To have courage for whatever comes in life - everything lies in that.', 69044, 0), (469169, 'Courage is on display every day, and only the courageous wring the most out of life.', 1692, 0), (469170, 'The trials on the road to world harmony are no greater than the courage of those who accept the challenge.', 38471, 0), (469171, 'I tend to think you''re fearless when you recognize why you should be scared of things, but do them anyway.', 67054, 0), (469172, 'Courage is poorly housed that dwells in numbers; the lion never counts the herd that are about him, nor weighs how many flocks he has to scatter.', 74115, 0), (469173, 'Curiosity, rationalization, and laziness are no match against courage, self-control, and mental toughness.', 881, 0), (469174, 'That''s what acting is - it''s about... having the courage to allow your audience into the private moments of your characters'' lives.', 37611, 0), (469175, 'Courage - you develop courage by doing small things like just as if you wouldn''t want to pick up a 100-pound weight without preparing yourself.', 74, 0), (469176, 'Courage and grace are a formidable mixture. The only place to see it is in the bullring.', 5858, 0), (469177, 'I was a little doubtful about the propriety of going to the Mammoth Cave without a gentleman escort, but if two ladies travel alone they must have the courage of men.', 6136, 0), (469178, 'Being tall has a major impact in general. It takes some courage to be as big as you are - to live up to it and not be intimidated by the graceful tiny people.', 62717, 0), (469179, 'In the military, you learn the essence of people. You see so many examples of self-sacrifice and moral courage. In the rest of life, you don''t get that many opportunities to be sure of your friends.', 69491, 0), (469180, 'Unjust. How many times I''ve used that word, scolded myself with it. All I mean by it now is that I don''t have the final courage to say that I refuse to preside over violations against myself, and to hell with justice.', 1991, 0), (469181, 'Decision is a risk rooted in the courage of being free.', 2750, 0), (469182, 'Ingenuity, plus courage, plus work, equals miracles.', 74116, 0), (469183, 'I have a hat. It is graceful and feminine and give me a certain dignity, as if I were attending a state funeral or something. Someday I may get up enough courage to wear it, instead of carrying it.', 152, 0), (469184, 'Caesar was a man of great common sense and good taste, meaning thereby a man without originality or moral courage.', 266, 0), (469185, 'In strife who inquires whether stratagem or courage was used?', 1462, 0), (469186, 'This soul, or life within us, by no means agrees with the life outside us. If one has the courage to ask her what she thinks, she is always saying the very opposite to what other people say.', 113, 0), (469187, 'A man of courage is also full of faith.', 1306, 0), (469188, 'Physical courage, which despises all danger, will make a man brave in one way; and moral courage, which despises all opinion, will make a man brave in another.', 432, 0), (469189, 'To him that waits all things reveal themselves, provided that he has the courage not to deny, in the darkness, what he has seen in the light.', 74117, 0), (469190, 'Real courage is knowing what faces you and knowing how to face it.', 74118, 0), (469191, 'I beg you take courage the brave soul can mend even disaster. ', 33381, 0), (469192, 'It takes vision and courage to create - it takes faith and courage to prove.', 62438, 0), (469193, 'Courage! I have shown it for years think you I shall lose it at the moment when my sufferings are to end? ', 19731, 0), (469194, 'You take a number of small steps which you believe are right, thinking maybe tomorrow somebody will treat this as a dangerous provocation. And then you wait. If there is no reaction, you take another step: courage is only an accumulation of small steps.', 36264, 0), (469195, 'There''s only one requirement of any of us, and that is to be courageous. Because courage, as you might know, defines all other human behavior. And, I believe - because I''ve done a little of this myself - pretending to be courageous is just as good as the real thing.', 17083, 0), (469196, 'Acting is really about having the courage to fail in front of people.', 69491, 0), (469197, 'I think we spend so much of our lives trying to pretend that we know what''s going to happen next. In fact we don''t. To recognize that we don''t know even what will happen this afternoon and yet having the courage to move forward - that''s one meaning of faith.', 124, 0), (469198, 'Next to courage, willpower is the most important thing in politics.', 14623, 0), (469199, 'The best marriages are the ones where we can go out in the world and really put ourselves out there. A lot of times we''ll fail, and sometimes we''ll pull it off. But good marriages are when you can go home and know that your vulnerability will be honored as courage, and that you''ll find support.', 247, 0), (469200, 'It shouldn''t take extreme courage and a willingness to go to prison for decades or even life to blow the whistle on bad government acts done in secret. But it does. And that is an immense problem for democracy, one that all journalists should be united in fighting.', 16048, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469201, 'What I am very, very moved and struck by is that so many people in the world are often living a life that they hadn''t planned for themselves. And they wake up one day and say, ''Hang on. Who am I? Is this really me? Is this what I really wanted?'' And also, ''Can I change it? Have I got the courage to change it?''', 22748, 0), (469202, 'The most memorable interviews for me are folks whose names I don''t know: young civil rights leaders in the South, showing great courage as they walked into a town in the dark of night. A doctor working for ''Doctors Without Borders'' in Somalia, operating by kerosene light in a tent. Those are the kinds of people that linger in your memory.', 11429, 0), (469203, 'Navigating a nonsober world of restaurants and bars, dinner parties, and benefits is like anything that requires practice. Like tennis or a foreign language, it gets easier the more you do it. But like all beginnings, it can be awkward. You stumble, you worry, and then there are unexpected moments of grace that give you the courage to keep going.', 14842, 0), (469204, 'Had we lived I should have had a tale to tell of the hardihood, endurance and courage of my companions which would have stirred the heart of every Englishman. These rough notes and our dead bodies must tell the tale.', 51384, 0), (469205, 'You will always be fond of me. I represent to you all the sins you have never had the courage to commit.', 40, 0), (469206, 'The gospel alone liberates you to live a life of scandalous generosity, unrestrained sacrifice, uncommon valor, and unbounded courage.', 16728, 0), (469207, 'There can be no great courage where there is no confidence or assurance, and half the battle is in the conviction that we can do what we undertake.', 4025, 0), (469208, 'In acting, there''s a type of courage you''re recognized for all the time. You lose 100 pounds and play a guy with AIDS, and you get rewarded. But, in life, doing what is courageous is quiet, and no one knows about it. Courage is someone making sacrifices for their family or making selfless decisions for what they hope or feel.', 12642, 0), (469209, 'Art, it seems to me, doesn''t need freedom so much as it needs courage and love - some would call it ''soul'' or ''Eros.''', 10407, 0), (469210, 'Loving the church also means having the courage to make difficult, trying choices, having ever before oneself the good of the church and not one''s own.', 856, 0), (469211, 'America needs jobs, smaller government, less spending and a president with the courage to offer more than yet another speech.', 67560, 0), (469212, 'Change will never happen when people lack the ability and courage to see themselves for who they are.', 24882, 0), (469213, 'Leaders are focused on using their vision and courage to do great things. This means challenging the way things are done and then sharing the journey with others.', 66659, 0), (469214, 'Work on something that matters. Have courage.', 66657, 0), (469215, 'For a long time, it was like I was part of some special forces unit: I''d land, meet everyone, five minutes later I''d have to do some amazing work, then - boom! - I''m out again. You know, playing supporting parts takes courage.', 70258, 0), (469216, 'We read our children stories starring elephants and monkeys and bears to teach them about nobility, curiosity and courage, to warn them against selfishness and stubbornness.', 4572, 0), (469217, 'I have no physical courage, I''ve asked for a double.', 3217, 0), (469218, 'I have the responsibility of over four million people, and I am in a position to do good, to be able to bring about a new life for my people, and I will continue to move in that direction. It''s a burden, but it needs to be done, and you have to have the courage and wisdom to see it through.', 30519, 0), (469219, 'I have had a lot of crushes but have never had the courage to go up to a girl and say what I feel. I am scared of rejection.', 69360, 0), (469220, 'The last thing a woman will consent to discover in a man whom she loves, or on whom she simply depends, is want of courage.', 1241, 0), (469221, 'John Glenn''s life will long be remembered for his time in space, his courage, and his service to all Americans.', 70564, 0), (469222, 'With his trademark courage and conviction, President Reagan led us out of the Cold War, spreading his vision of freedom, resulting in the release of millions of people from the yoke of communism.', 68704, 0), (469223, 'We can never intimidate and discourage the people who voice their words with courage. The essence of freedom rests precisely here - in the freedom of expression of the people. And we must protect it.', 67491, 0), (469224, 'Wisdom, prudence, forethought, these are essential. But not second to these that noble courage which adventures the right, and leaves the consequences to God.', 67935, 0), (469225, 'These rules may seem simple enough, but it will require great morale and physical courage to adhere to them. But if carried out in the strict sense of the word it will surely lead to a greater success than could otherwise be attained.', 71342, 0), (469226, 'If the City Council wants to hold the police accountable, it has the subpoena power and oversight responsibility to do so. They don''t have the courage to do it.', 71003, 0), (469227, 'The courage to be is rooted in the God who appears when God has disappeared in the anxiety of doubt.', 2750, 0), (469228, 'I try to be a truthful artist and I try to show a level of courage. I enjoy that. I''m a messenger.', 70612, 0), (469229, 'Courage is often lack of insight, whereas cowardice in many cases is based on good information.', 2206, 0), (469230, 'Being a leader for me is about having the courage to speak the truth, and live the truth, despite attempts to silence our thoughts, feelings, and past experiences.', 29215, 0), (469231, 'The one man other than my father who made the most lasting impression was an uncle, Serge B. Benson. He taught me in three different classes - but above all, he taught me lessons in moral, physical, and intellectual courage that I have tried to apply in later life.', 1826, 0), (469232, 'Let''s drink to the spirit of gallantry and courage that made a strange Heaven out of unbelievable Hell, and let''s drink to the hope that one day this country of ours, which we love so much, will find dignity and greatness and peace again.', 2896, 0), (469233, 'To be a Bond girl you need courage, charm, determination and feistiness.', 68945, 0), (469234, 'We are in the midst of a momentous catastrophe of world history, of a transformation of all aspects of life and of the entire inner human being This is perhaps fortunate for the artistic person, if he is strong enough to bear the consequences, because what we need is the courage to have inner experience.', 10311, 0), (469235, 'The power of the human spirit inspires me. Movies, books, stories, people, anything that reminds us that we are more than just this physical body and our capacity for love and courage can bend reality.', 69400, 0), (469236, 'I think my mother... made it clear that you have to live life by your own terms and you have to not worry about what other people think and you have to have the courage to do the unexpected.', 10105, 0), (469237, 'If I have brought any message today, it is this: Have the courage to have your wisdom regarded as stupidity. Be fools for Christ. And have the courage to suffer the contempt of the sophisticated world.', 21037, 0), (469238, 'Everyone has talent. What is rare is the courage to follow the talent to the dark place where it leads.', 405, 0), (469239, 'The joy of style lies not in how we look to other people, but in how we look to ourselves - and the most memorable and beautiful outfits are simply those that, in some rare moment of joy, we found the courage to share with the world.', 4035, 0), (469240, 'One man scorned and covered with scars still strove with his last ounce of courage to reach the unreachable stars and the world will be better for this. ', 62284, 0), (469241, 'Believe in individual initiatives, in courage, in risk.', 68911, 0), (469242, 'He who loses wealth loses much he who loses a friend loses more but he that loses his courage loses all. ', 62284, 0), (469243, 'Innovation is so hard and so frustrating; it takes the intersections of people with courage, vision, and resources.', 68867, 0), (469244, 'We need the compassion and the courage to change the conditions that support our suffering. Those conditions are things like ignorance, bitterness, negligence, clinging, and holding on.', 124, 0), (469245, 'I want to grow old without facelifts. I want to have the courage to be loyal to the face I have made.', 1, 0), (469246, 'I have always had the courage for the new things that life sometimes offers.', 62856, 0), (469247, 'Peace comes when you talk to the guy you most hate. And that''s where the courage of a leader comes, because when you sit down with your enemy, you as a leader must already have very considerable confidence from your own constituency.', 2109, 0), (469248, 'Have the courage to act instead of react.', 24754, 0), (469249, 'Courage is doing what you are afraid to do. There can be no courage unless you are scared.', 63037, 0), (469250, 'We have to confront ourselves. Do we like what we see in the mirror? And, according to our light, according to our understanding, according to our courage, we will have to say yea or nay - and rise!', 74, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469251, 'When everything goes wrong, what a joy to test your soul and see if it has endurance and courage. An invisible and all-powerful enemy - some call him God, others the Devil, seem to rush upon us to destroy us; but we are not destroyed.', 1048, 0), (469252, 'Just remaining quietly in the presence of God, listening to Him, being attentive to Him, requires a lot of courage and know-how.', 123, 0), (469253, 'Courage is the ladder on which all the other virtues mount.', 21495, 0), (469254, 'Who could refrain that had a heart to love and in that heart courage to make love known?', 13, 0), (469255, 'No man in the world has more courage than the man who can stop after eating one peanut.', 9956, 0), (469256, 'I have the courage of my convictions.', 15813, 0), (469257, 'We must remind Americans that the promise of opportunity remains unbroken - that every person in this great nation can succeed through hard work, courage and personal responsibility.', 67720, 0), (469258, 'I have seen in the Halls of Congress more idealism, more humanness, more compassion, more profiles of courage than in any other institution that I have ever known.', 15498, 0), (469259, 'It often takes more courage to change one''s opinion than to keep it.', 74119, 0), (469260, 'We need to find the courage to say no to the things and people that are not serving us if we want to rediscover ourselves and live our lives with authenticity.', 28913, 0), (469261, 'Often times I have been asked about the attributes for success, and I have said that you need two attributes for succeeding as an entrepreneur: one, courage, second, luck.', 66606, 0), (469262, 'I can muster up the courage in the difficult situations to get me through.', 8452, 0), (469263, 'Suffering! We owe to it all that is good in us, all that gives value to life; we owe to it pity, we owe to it courage, we owe to it all the virtues.', 348, 0), (469264, 'It takes both courage and talent to stand up in front of fellow human beings and make them crack a smile, and at the same time keep it clean.', 4199, 0), (469265, 'It takes as much courage to have tried and failed as it does to have tried and succeeded.', 1407, 0), (469266, 'Every human being on this earth is born with a tragedy, and it isn''t original sin. He''s born with the tragedy that he has to grow up... a lot of people don''t have the courage to do it.', 4743, 0), (469267, 'Success, they taught me, is built on the foundation of courage, hard-work and individual responsibility. Despite what some would have us believe, success is not built on resentment and fears.', 66800, 0), (469268, 'Valor lies just halfway between rashness and cowardice.', 62284, 0), (469269, 'Courage consists not in blindly overlooking danger, but in seeing it, and conquering it.', 62538, 0), (469270, 'What is more mortifying than to feel that you have missed the plum for want of courage to shake the tree?', 1014, 0), (469271, 'True courage is a result of reasoning. A brave mind is always impregnable.', 63086, 0), (469272, 'Courage can''t see around corners but goes around them anyway.', 1932, 0), (469273, 'Men was formed for society, and is neither capable of living alone, nor has the courage to do it.', 73513, 0), (469274, 'The courage of very ordinary people is all that stands between us and the dark.', 15447, 0), (469275, 'One of the hardest questions I have been asked is ''How will you manage the army if you are having menstrual cramps?'' I have also been asked if I will have the courage to face criminals. My answer is that courage is not a matter of gender.', 74079, 0), (469276, 'Americans are gathering the courage to just say no. We are saying no to addictive consumer lifestyles. We are saying no to wars and corporate takeover and the IMF loans that gobble up people and their resources.', 74120, 0), (469277, 'When I write, what I long for is not more realism or fiction but more courage. That''s what I always find myself short on and what I have to struggle to achieve in order that the work might live.', 560, 0), (469278, 'I believe the biggest challenge is just getting the courage to try something different or new. Try to forget the stereotype in your mind. Yoga is for everyone - children, athletes, moms, dads, accountants, truck drivers, even country stars.', 67526, 0), (469279, 'When our mothers are alive and healthy, they do extraordinary things... like the mothers of Plaza de Mayo, who marched in Argentinean plazas, defying the military junta dictatorship and demanding the whereabouts of their abducted children... or the Liberian mothers who faced down civil war armed only with T-shirts and courage.', 71869, 0), (469280, 'The word ''courage,'' one of my favorite words, the root or the etymology of that word is ''cour,'' which means heart. I think true courage is actually following your heart and not getting or succumbing to what other people''s definition of what your life should be. Live your life.', 68255, 0), (469281, 'Having the courage to say no when all your friends are saying yes is one of the most difficult things you''ll ever have to do. Doing it, however, is one of the biggest charges you can ever make to your personal battery. I call this ''won''t power.''', 6058, 0), (469282, 'War isn''t just about bravery and courage and jingoism and patriotism. It''s also fundamentally about grief. And the people that go and do the fighting and the dying are never the people who actually benefit from the fighting and the dying.', 67669, 0), (469283, 'Everywhere I go, I always look for creative entrepreneurs, whether it''s artisans and craftsmen, small farmers and gardeners, or restaurateurs who use fresh, locally sourced ingredients. I admire the courage and self-reliance it takes to start your own business and make it succeed.', 37848, 0), (469284, 'Based on my experience, I believe that Ben Sasse has the right policy background, a notable commitment to public service - and, perhaps most importantly, the courage - to help renew our country.', 69881, 0), (469285, 'The younger you are, the more courage and audacity you will have to set long-term goals and be there to personally work towards your vision. You will have the confidence to take risks because you have time by your side. You can bring innovation into everything you do and constantly reinvent yourself.', 67050, 0), (469286, 'Grave was the man in years, in looks, in word, his locks were grey, yet was his courage green.', 915, 0), (469287, 'Our situation today shows that beauty demands for itself at least as much courage and decision as do truth and goodness, and she will not allow herself to be separated and banned from her two sisters without taking them along with herself in an act of mysterious vengeance.', 1758, 0), (469288, 'Although most executives pay lip service to the idea of hiring for cultural fit, few have the courage or discipline to make it the primary criteria for bringing someone into the company.', 17487, 0), (469289, 'The truth won''t set us free - until we develop the skills and the habit and the talent and the moral courage to use it.', 23135, 0), (469290, 'When I was younger, I was kind of fearless. I think it takes more courage to do things when you know more. I was completely naive, and I was like, ''Why can''t I do anything I want to do?''', 67918, 0), (469291, 'More firm and sure the hand of courage strikes, when it obeys the watchful eye of caution.', 63383, 0), (469292, 'Resignation is the courage of Christian sorrow.', 74121, 0), (469293, 'There is in true beauty, as in courage, something which narrow souls cannot dare to admire.', 14081, 0), (469294, 'As a shame researcher, I know that the very best thing to do in the midst of a shame attack is totally counterintuitive: Practice courage and reach out!', 247, 0), (469295, 'It requires greater courage to preserve inner freedom, to move on in one''s inward journey into new realms, than to stand defiantly for outer freedom. It is often easier to play the martyr, as it is to be rash in battle.', 2467, 0), (469296, 'Courage is not the absence of despair; it is, rather, the capacity to move ahead in spite of despair.', 2467, 0), (469297, 'A great part of courage is the courage of having done the thing before.', 760, 0), (469298, 'Courage is the capacity to confront what can be imagined.', 1898, 0), (469299, 'The only courage that matters is the kind that gets you from one moment to the next.', 1932, 0), (469300, 'Courage is the greatest of all virtues, because if you haven''t courage, you may not have an opportunity to use any of the others.', 2087, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469301, 'Courage and conviction are powerful weapons against an enemy who depends only on fists or guns. Animals know when you are afraid a coward knows when you are not. ', 63103, 0), (469302, 'You have to really be courageous about your instincts and your ideas. Otherwise you''ll just knuckle under, and things that might have been memorable will be lost.', 28610, 0), (469303, 'I feel quite fearless protecting the people I love.', 69336, 0), (469304, 'Have the courage to be ignorant of a great number of things, in order to avoid the calamity of being ignorant of everything.', 9771, 0), (469305, 'The courage to imagine the otherwise is our greatest resource, adding color and suspense to all our life.', 10820, 0), (469306, 'There is nothing in the world so much admired as a man who knows how to bear unhappiness with courage.', 65434, 0), (469307, 'If we are to survive, we must have ideas, vision, and courage. These things are rarely produced by committees. Everything that matters in our intellectual and moral life begins with an individual confronting his own mind and conscience in a room by himself.', 70874, 0), (469308, 'The paradox of courage is that a man must be a little careless of his life even in order to keep it.', 67663, 0), (469309, 'To persevere, trusting in what hopes he has, is courage in a man.', 542, 0), (469310, 'Courage enlarges, cowardice diminishes resources. In desperate straits the fears of the timid aggravate the dangers that imperil the brave.', 6105, 0), (469311, 'The amount of eccentricity in a society has generally been proportional to the amount of genius, mental vigor, and moral courage it contained. That so few now dare to be eccentric marks the chief danger of the time.', 1880, 0), (469312, 'Support the strong, give courage to the timid, remind the indifferent, and warn the opposed.', 74122, 0), (469313, 'My talent is such that no undertaking, however vast in size... has ever surpassed my courage.', 65057, 0), (469314, 'Greatness, in the last analysis, is largely bravery - courage in escaping from old ideas and old standards and respectable ways of doing things.', 63066, 0), (469315, 'I would kiss you, had I the courage.', 19835, 0), (469316, 'Your determination, selflessness and courage have brought the freedom struggle towards its fulfilment.', 71320, 0), (469317, 'Rosa Parks'' courage, determination, and tenacity continue to be an inspiration to all those committed to non-violent protest and change nearly half a century later.', 69116, 0), (469318, 'One of the things that makes Hamlet unique among Shakespeare''s characters is his courage to face up to the darker elements of his personality.', 63679, 0), (469319, 'Courage stands halfway between cowardice and rashness, one of which is a lack, the other an excess of courage.', 4891, 0), (469320, 'It is a wise man who knows where courage ends and stupidity begins.', 73723, 0), (469321, 'Traits like humility, courage, and empathy are easily overlooked - but it''s immensely important to find them in your closest relationships.', 10905, 0), (469322, 'I think that the romantic impulse is in all of us and that sometimes we live it for a short time, but it''s not part of a sensible way of living. It''s a heroic path and it generally ends dangerously. I treasure it in the sense that I believe it''s a path of great courage. It can also be the path of the foolhardy and the compulsive.', 72476, 0), (469323, 'September 11, 2001, revealed heroism in ordinary people who might have gone through their lives never called upon to demonstrate the extent of their courage.', 10676, 0), (469324, 'Remember that the good angels do what they can to preserve men from sin and obtain God''s honor. But they do not lose courage when men fail.', 70538, 0), (469325, 'It takes some courage to write fiction about politically controversial topics. The dread is you''ll be labeled a political writer.', 679, 0), (469326, 'The true legacy of 9-11 cannot be found among political leaders of the day, but in the citizen soldiers and public safety personnel who answered that day with courage and selflessness.', 66593, 0), (469327, 'One of the things your unconscious mind does for you - and it''s a great gift - is it gives you extra courage to view the outer world and it does that by giving you an extra-special view of yourself.', 26113, 0), (469328, '''Beyond the Lights'' took incredible fight to get made. Four years of writing and two years of overcoming ''no.'' Every studio balked. Twice. But I kept fighting. What gave me the courage was ''Love & Basketball.'' Every studio turned down that film, too. But I never gave up because I believed in it with my whole heart and soul.', 74123, 0), (469329, 'It takes a lot of courage, when everyone is asking you what you want to do, if you say that you want to be a musician or an actor; people can be very condescending and say, ''Oh, that''s so sweet, good luck with that!'' It can be very frustrating.', 74124, 0), (469330, 'When the economic well-being of their nation demanded a strong and creative response, my colleagues at the Federal Reserve... mustered the moral courage to do what was necessary.', 66590, 0), (469331, 'Wanted: a man who will not lose his individuality in a crowd, a man who has the courage of his convictions, who is not afraid to say ''No,'' though all the world say ''Yes.''', 4025, 0), (469332, 'When I was a young man, Dirac was my hero. He made a breakthrough, a new method of doing physics. He had the courage to simply guess at the form of an equation, the equation we now call the Dirac equation, and to try to interpret it afterwards.', 66888, 0), (469333, 'Poetry takes courage because you have to face things and you try to articulate how you feel.', 19836, 0), (469334, 'My mother''s father, Hobart Cromwell, was a bacteriologist with Abbott Laboratories in suburban Chicago. I never got to know him well, as he died very young, but he was always a heroic figure in our family, wise and gentle and intelligent by reputation, with the courage to fight against the McCarthyites.', 71253, 0), (469335, 'During the course of 1989, more and more East Germans lost their fears of the state''s repression and chicanery and went out on the streets. There was no turning back then. It is thanks to their courage the Wall was opened.', 67556, 0), (469336, 'The five patients in ''Rethinking Cancer'' share with us the path of their recovery: the courage to take their own lives in their hands with a natural approach to healing their bodies.', 67023, 0), (469337, 'I learned that sometimes our struggles are a little bit bigger than us and talking about them and coming through and having the courage to get out of them. I learned how many I touched and inspired through the journey of ''Idol'' because I was just singing on the show. I wasn''t really being an advocate for anything.', 74125, 0), (469338, 'What we want from modern dance is courage and audacity.', 7842, 0), (469339, 'I many times encountered courage, real courage. Undeniable courage. I''ve heard it said that that was the highest quality of the human animal. I encountered that many times, in unexpected places. And I have learned to recognize it when I see it.', 1142, 0), (469340, 'Courage is simply the willingness to be afraid and act anyway.', 5857, 0), (469341, 'We need men with moral courage to speak and write their real thoughts, and to stand by their convictions, even to the very death.', 67335, 0), (469342, 'Limit to courage? There is no limit to courage.', 74126, 0), (469343, 'The problem is when you are writing something in retrospective, it needs a lot of courage not to change, or you will forget a certain reality, and you will just take in consideration your view today.', 74127, 0), (469344, 'Most of man''s problems upon this planet, in the long history of the race, have been met and solved either partially or as a whole by experiment based on common sense and carried out with courage.', 74128, 0), (469345, 'Parents do not have the courage to say no to certain things that their children demand. They are rather scared of their children.', 1998, 0), (469346, 'To me, having the courage to tell your own story goes hand in hand with having the curiosity and humility to listen to others'' stories.', 308, 0), (469347, 'You will find as you grow older that courage is the rarest of all qualities to be found in public life.', 1827, 0), (469348, 'Until there are no more hate crimes, no more vicious bullying and ugly slurs, whenever a person comes out - whether that person is a celebrity or a ''nobody'' - it should be celebrated like the triumph of courage it is.', 67006, 0), (469349, 'I considered our British comrades to rank with the finest men and women of any armed service in the world. And I know that my fellow American soldiers - and those of the other coalition countries under my command - valued very highly the professional expertise, capability, courage, and determination of our British partners on the battlefield.', 68916, 0), (469350, 'Either life entails courage, or it ceases to be life.', 102, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469351, 'What I love about the East End is that there''s a great perseverance, determination and courage. What I dislike about it is that there is sometimes a celebration of ignorance.', 74129, 0), (469352, 'I wish we lived in a society that made it safe and provided the courage for everyone to come out.', 71288, 0), (469353, 'It takes courage to know when you ought to be afraid.', 2239, 0), (469354, 'Every man has his own courage, and is betrayed because he seeks in himself the courage of other persons.', 760, 0), (469355, 'What happened in the missile crisis in October 1962 has been prettified to make it look as if acts of courage and thoughtfulness abounded. The truth is that the whole episode was almost insane.', 1955, 0), (469356, 'Some people have a hard time getting rid of stuff. If that''s you, pray for God to give you the courage to get rid of things you don''t really need or things He wants you to give away. This will help keep your surroundings organized and clutter-free.', 1206, 0), (469357, 'The only service a friend can really render is to keep up your courage by holding up to you a mirror in which you can see a noble image of yourself.', 266, 0), (469358, 'The psychologist Elizabeth Loftus has shown great courage, in the face of spiteful vested interests, in demonstrating how easy it is for people to concoct memories that are entirely false but which seem, to the victim, every bit as real as true memories.', 1716, 0), (469359, 'Darwin gives courage to the rest of science that we shall end up understanding literally everything, springing from almost nothing - a thought extremely hard to comprehend and believe.', 1716, 0), (469360, 'Perfect courage is to do without witnesses what one would be capable of doing with the world looking on.', 154, 0), (469361, 'What I''ve always said is that I''m opposed to institutional racism, and I would''ve, had I''ve been alive at the time, I think, had the courage to march with Martin Luther King to overturn institutional racism, and I see no place in our society for institutional racism.', 67555, 0), (469362, 'The courage of the Syrian protesters is remarkable, for they face prison, torture, or death every time they lift a banner.', 67439, 0), (469363, 'My father once said something very shrewd about me to a woman journalist who had told him how courageous she thought I was for always speaking my mind. My father said, ''If you couldn''t care less what anyone says about you, then it''s not courage.''', 2074, 0), (469364, 'Courage is almost a contradiction in terms. It means a strong desire to live taking the form of readiness to die.', 67663, 0), (469365, 'Many a man will have the courage to die gallantly, but will not have the courage to say, or even to think, that the cause for which he is asked to die is an unworthy one.', 95, 0), (469366, 'Courage without conscience is a wild beast.', 67335, 0), (469367, 'It is a blessed thing that in every age some one has had the individuality enough and courage enough to stand by his own convictions.', 67335, 0), (469368, 'Roscoe Conkling was a man of superb courage. He not only acted without fear, but he had that fortitude of soul which bears the consequences of the course pursued without complaint.', 67335, 0), (469369, 'To find the courage to do what I want to do for myself has been hard.', 46525, 0), (469370, 'We''re going to be OK because of the American people. They have more grit, determination and courage than you can imagine.', 17532, 0), (469371, 'Every man ultimately falls into the company with which he affiliates. And he is the strongest who draws men to himself, who creates the company; and this is through having a positive quality - courage and physical prowess.', 4025, 0), (469372, 'You got to have a lot of courage. Secondly, whatever it is you''re doing, you have to believe in it wholeheartedly. Thirdly, you have to be able to stand up in front of people and know that they''ll laugh.', 53024, 0), (469373, 'A wise woman knows how to summon her courage and do what is right, rather than what is easy.', 10090, 0), (469374, 'In all realms of life it takes courage to stretch your limits, express your power, and fulfill your potential... it''s no different in the financial realm.', 10090, 0), (469375, 'A wise woman recognizes when her life is out of balance and summons the courage to act to correct it, she knows the meaning of true generosity, happiness is the reward for a life lived in harmony, with a courage and grace.', 10090, 0), (469376, 'Courage is not always about action. It takes courage to do nothing rather than do something that you do not believe in or understand.', 10090, 0), (469377, 'There are looks that I see on other people that I think would look horrible on me, but I think if somebody has the courage to be really daring and try something outlandish, then more power to them. That''s just encouraging and inspiring.', 38496, 0), (469378, 'The first thing out of Fidel Castro''s mouth to me, he looked me right in the eye and said, ''You''re a man of great courage.''', 16709, 0), (469379, 'When you question this war on poverty, you get all the criticisms from adherents to the status quo who just don''t want to see anything change. We got to have the courage to face that down, just as we did in the welfare reform of the late 1990s, and if we succeeded, we can help resuscitate this culture and get people back to work.', 66572, 0), (469380, 'The courage we desire and prize is not the courage to die decently, but to live manfully.', 3061, 0), (469381, 'The Brazilian poet Vinicius de Moraes wrote that beauty is fundamental. Well, with the poet''s permission, so is courage.', 18085, 0), (469382, 'Political courage is not political suicide.', 12194, 0), (469383, 'In 1984, showing extraordinary courage, a group of Guatemalan wives, mothers and other relatives of disappeared people banded together to form the Mutual Support Group 