auditions section.', 69933, 0), (469432, 'I could never muster the courage to speak to girls in my college in Pune. Most of them were Parsis and spoke English. I came from a village and could barely converse in English.', 67045, 0), (469433, 'Athletes are used to battling. The public would never learn their names if professional athletes had not shown courage at an early age. They learn they can overcome, but sometimes this becomes a false sense of security that leads them to the edge.', 67719, 0), (469434, 'Unfortunately, unless we''re focused on building up our courage, which gives us our self-confidence and all that we need to make quantum change in our lives, the voice of fear will always take the lead inside our minds.', 5671, 0), (469435, 'What I would say to anybody facing any life challenge or disease is that that is courage - to choose life, to keep looking at what''s good.', 5671, 0), (469436, 'People say, ''You have inspired me, you''ve given me courage...'' They''ve gone so far as to say, ''You''ve changed my life!'' And I would come back and say to my husband, ''I can''t understand it - what kind of poor little life did she have if I had to come and change it?''', 67408, 0), (469437, 'Love bravely, live bravely, be courageous, there''s really nothing to lose. There''s no wrong you can''t make right again, so be kinder to yourself, you know, have fun, take chances. There''s no bounds.', 7655, 0), (469438, 'If you see a person who''s insecure and covers it up, it can be quite a problem. But the person who is insecure and shows you is quite appealing. They give you just the courage to drop your defenses.', 70259, 0), (469439, 'Lily Tomlin was one of the early comedy greats who influenced my courage to be the person I am.', 69033, 0), (469440, 'Red carpet is a little bit scary. It''s not about expression. It''s about taking a pretty picture in a really weird, awkward way, with so many people watching. It''s a glamorous part of the job, but it requires its own kind of courage.', 69033, 0), (469441, 'Courage that grows from constitution often forsakes a man when he has occasion for it courage which arises from a sense of duty acts in a uniform manner. ', 2868, 0), (469442, 'All I''m saying is that there are many different kinds of political theatre and many plays I greatly admire: ''Antigone,'' ''Mother Courage,'' ''All My Sons.'' But, if I tackle a political theme, I have to do it in my own way.', 3174, 0), (469443, 'There was one man in the Labour government, Robin Cook, whom I had a very high regard for. He had the courage to speak out and to resign over Iraq. He was an admirable man. But resignation over a matter of principle is not a very fashionable thing in our society.', 3174, 0), (469444, 'Everybody''s opinion is equally valid, and I feel like everybody should have an opportunity to speak out, and everyone should have the courage to speak out.', 21674, 0), (469445, 'Some of the greatest survivors have been women. Look at the courage so many women have shown after surviving earthquakes in the rubble for days on end.', 9272, 0), (469446, 'I''m sick of all these labels and these manufactured subdivisions of music that don''t even exist. And even though I''m pierced myself, I''m sick of everyone equating body piercing with musical courage. If you ask me, it takes a lot more than that.', 3572, 0), (469447, 'Lying at the root of the social agreements of 1980 are the courage, sense of responsibility, and the solidarity of the working people. Both sides have then recognized that an accord must be reached if bloodshed is to be prevented.', 63581, 0), (469448, 'For years, I was watching other people have so much fun playing out their version of authorship, like Louis C.K. and Larry David. As I watched them do their thing, I began to pine for the days when I had a lot less expected of me and, often, a lot more creative freedom. The courage that those guys have is always captivating to me.', 68269, 0), (469449, 'America''s