INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469451, 'The Chinaman has only a passive courage, but this courage he possesses in the highest degree. His indifference to death is truly extraordinary. When he is ill, he sees it approach, and does not falter. When condemned, and already in the hands of an officer, he manifests no fear.', 3205, 0), (469452, 'Who asks whether the enemy was defeated by strategy or valor?', 1462, 0), (469453, 'I think what - I think what the American people is looking for is they are looking for moral and intellectual courage and clarity, and not a sense of passivity or confusion.', 68938, 0), (469454, 'People have responded to my stories so well. They come up after a show and say things like, ''Your album really helped me,'' or ''I have stage four cancer. I''m terminally ill.'' Somebody told me it gave them the courage to die.', 67056, 0), (469455, 'Rather like Batman, I embody the themes of the movie which are the values of family, courage and compassion and a sense of right and wrong, good and bad and justice.', 3625, 0), (469456, 'I''m not going to be bullied or pushed around by the group of the day. You''ve got to have political courage. You''ve got to have your own inner beliefs.', 66982, 0), (469457, 'I don''t like baseball movies. I like movies about moral courage and people who are indomitable and courageous and right.', 12392, 0), (469458, 'I learned that moral courage is harder than physical courage.', 3159, 0), (469459, 'I think there''s a growing courage among the younger generation of American writers. Because of the more superficial treatment of characters taking place in cinema, they have had to deal with that by digging deeper into who these people are.', 5980, 0), (469460, 'Perhaps what distinguishes my characters is their courage and spirit and a certain stubbornness which enables them to keep going even when facing a setback. I think this developed organically as I wrote, but also it came out of a desire to portray women as powerful and intelligent forces in the world.', 2041, 0), (469461, 'I realise that a novel and a film are different mediums. As artistes, we need to respect other artistes. It also needs a lot of courage to take risks to experiment and interpret known literary works.', 2041, 0), (469462, 'Trump has the courage to stand up to Wall Street, to the K Street lobbyists, and say our trade deals have not been best for the ordinary, average citizen American.', 72457, 0), (469463, 'If the anti-Christian agenda will say, ''Here''s your identity, you''re an evolved amoeba who ought to just go do whatever you want and don''t let anybody tell you different,'' then they can get you to throw your faith, your character, your courage, and your liberty right out the window.', 1949, 0), (469464, 'Faith in God... produces character; character will produce courage, courage to face the challenges of the day.', 1949, 0), (469465, 'Heroes to me are guys that sit in libraries. They absorb knowledge and then the risks they take are calculated on the basis of the courage it took to become replete with knowledge.', 67061, 0), (469466, 'Every man of courage is a man of his word.', 3285, 0), (469467, 'Being able to hear someone say, ''I found an incredible job on The Muse,'' or ''It gave me courage to make a career change,'' that''s the motivating factor.', 67682, 0), (469468, 'We must have the courage to confront dreadful views even in the people we love the most. But that''s difficult to do when we cast large segments of our fellow citizens into a basket to be condemned and disparaged, judging them even as we ignore that many of their deplorable traits exist in us, too.', 9371, 0), (469469, 'I''m slowly working up the courage to sing in front of other people, but I can carry a tune. I do some mean karaoke.', 72716, 0), (469470, 'The condition of all development is not to be content with the present, but to have the courage to ask how everything can be made better and the good 