S. and Israel are not punished: no international court has the courage to put them on trial.', 8072, 0), (469663, 'I find fault with my children because I like them and I want them to go places - uprightness and strength and courage and civil respect and anything that affects the probabilities of failure on the part of those that are closest to me, that concerns me - I find fault.', 62664, 0), (469664, 'Just two weeks ago, millions of Iraqis defied the threats of terrorists and went to the polls to determine their own future. I congratulate the Iraqi people for the courage they''ve shown in making these elections so successful.', 67591, 0), (469665, 'Most of the good executives do pretty well. Because to be a good executive you have to be strong, and you have to have a simple attribute that people have forgotten about - courage.', 72619, 0), (469666, 'That was the fun of acting, being a blank canvas you could transform into the character - Indian princess, 20s vamp, Mother Courage, Oxford don, 94-year-old wife.', 73008, 0), (469667, 'You want to shut up every Negro who has the courage to stand up and fight for the rights of his people, for the rights of workers, and I have been on many a picket line for the steelworkers too.', 3412, 0), (469668, 'I have a lot of courage. I''m a realist.', 59655, 0), (469669, 'It is right to endure with resignation what the gods send, and to face one''s enemies with courage.', 16758, 0), (469670, 'But we got up there and decided to stick to this mix of power chords and funk and that''s where it really started for us. In having the courage to take that decision. To take a gamble not just with our music but our lives.', 67188, 0), (469671, 'Our young people have come to look upon war as a kind of beneficent deity, which not only adds to the national honor but uplifts a nation and develops patriotism and courage.', 23215, 0), (469672, 'What I do know is that writing is the thing I am best at, and I don''t have the stomach, the ability, the strength or the courage to enter the political arena. And I think writing can be a political act, if only to let those people accountable know they are being watched. Literature can be a conscience.', 1592, 0), (469673, 'On sensitive issues, talk isn''t cheap - it takes real courage to pry open topics nailed shut.', 68782, 0), (469674, 'I am haunted by what my life would have been had I not had the courage in my early twenties to leave Pittsburgh for New York City and really commit to being a writer. Pittsburgh is both post-industrial and provincial, and the opportunities there are limited. It would have been quite easy to simply drift through life.', 70331, 0), (469675, 'I feel like Obama in a way. His idea that hope means not shrinking from a fight it''s the courage to reach for something. My music is that. Those are principles I try to embody. ', 69199, 0), (469676, 'Paul persuaded me to join the band. I would never have had the courage otherwise. It was fun at the beginning. We were playing just for fun, with Paul''s group.', 52060, 0), (469677, 'I love Joan Collins. She''s a wonderful lady. She has such courage. She''s such a good actress.', 69012, 0), (469678, 'There''s only one thing worse than a man who doesn''t have strong likes and dislikes, and that''s a man who has strong likes and dislikes without the courage to voice them.', 71450, 0), (469679, 'I think what I would say to my younger self, and probably to younger, just starting-out writers is that a lot of times you''re just afraid to put yourself out there, and it''s uncomfortable because it''s working up the courage to do something, to push yourself to do those things.', 74149, 0), (469680, 'The President regards the Japanese as a brave people; but courage, though useful in time of war, is subordinate to knowledge of arts; hence, courage without such knowledge is not to be highly esteemed.', 67501, 0), (469681, 'Before I begin talking about the threats we face, the vulnerabilities that we have, and frankly the courage of the men and women in uniform that stand in harm''s way on behalf of a very grateful Nation, let me first honor the sacrifices of September 11.', 72903, 0), (469682, 'All I needed was the courage to be me. That courage took a lifetime to develop.', 74150, 0), (469683, 'Courage is heartworth making itself felt in deeds. It never waits for chances it makes chances. ', 62529, 0), (469684, 'At the bottom of not a little of the bravery that appears in the world, there lurks a miserable cowardice. Men will face powder and steel because they have not the courage to face public opinion.', 43384, 0), (469685, 'Those who are rooted in the depths that are eternal and unchangeable and who rely on unshakeable principles, face change full of courage, courage based on faith.', 67379, 0), (469686, 'There is a measure needing courage to adopt and enforce it, which I believe to be of virtue sufficient to redeem the nation in this its darkest hour: one only; I know of no other to which we may rationally trust for relief from impending dangers without and within.', 67935, 0), (469687, 'Probably most dying patients, even when suffering greatly, would choose to live as long as possible. That courage and grace should be protected and honored, and we should put every effort into treating their symptoms.', 4691, 0), (469688, 'I have spent a great deal of my life being part of minorities. Some of the people I admire the most in the world have had the courage to defend, against wind and tide, minority viewpoints in those frightening times when any disagreement with universal conformity is identified as treason.', 68604, 0), (469689, 'All art is political. Yes. Even the stuff that sounds like bubble-gum songs. I think all art is, by nature, intended to motivate society for change, and the only reason change doesn''t happen is because within the target population, courage is lacking.', 74151, 0), (469690, 'My mom being raised in England, her father always wanted to pursue the arts and wanted to have a stage career in England. According to her, he never had the courage to actually pursue it full-time. I think that my grandfather''s parents thought that it wasn''t a formidable job to have.', 67936, 0), (469691, 'You don''t get happy by sitting around going on, ''Oh this is a horrible situation, what to do?'' You''ve got to find the courage to change that. I think change is extremely hard for people.', 70117, 0), (469692, 'I think all art is, by nature, intended to motivate society for change, and the only reason change doesn''t happen is because within the target population, courage is lacking.', 74151, 0), (469693, 'In short, we need to recover the courage we celebrate in our heroes, and in particular, the courage to tolerate, for the sake of a free society, a level of risk we hardly ever imagined in the past.', 38978, 0), (469694, 'I feel most alive, most electric with faith, breath, and courage, when I think of God as a current that runs through all that is. Not by will or by choice. Not as a benediction but because there are laws even God must obey.', 41866, 0), (469695, 'Back in school, there was this guy who had a huge crush on me. One day, when he mustered the courage to propose to me on a Rose Day, my friends burst out laughing right in front of him. I''m sure we all have had such experiences, and I''ve had crushes in the past. Right now, all I can think about is my films and deliver my best.', 68127, 0), (469696, 'A military coup needs a sacrifice and courage that you can''t find in an army without morale.', 70993, 0), (469697, 'To go to hospitals and see people fight and overcome cystic fibrosis or cancer or any number of illnesses is to see courage that is humbling. And athletes constantly need to be humbled.', 67211, 0), (469698, 'It was actually a women''s writing group I belonged to in graduate school that gave me the courage to move from poetry to fiction.', 28304, 0), (469699, 'I have written a memoir here and there, and that takes its own form of selfishness and courage. However, generally speaking, I have no interest in writing about my own life or intruding in the privacy of those around me.', 19143, 0), (469700, 'I see courage everywhere I go in Africa.', 74152, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469701, 'I see courage everywhere I go in Africa. Fearless human rights activists in Darfur. Women peace advocates in eastern Congo. Former child soldiers in Northern Uganda who now are helping other former child soldiers return to civilian life.', 74152, 0), (469702, 'As a person, I am someone who wants to give my the best in every take. I wouldn''t say it was easy for me to get into the industry because I come from a background where no one has been in films. But I do believe if you work hard, you will get noticed. Modeling gave me that courage to stand in front of the camera.', 68127, 0), (469703, 'Courage to be is the key to revelatory power of the feminist revolution.', 1492, 0), (469704, 'The Adequate Protest demands far more than protests. It calls for Great and Daring Leaps of Integrity and Courage to See.', 1492, 0), (469705, 'It is easy enough to praise men for the courage of their convictions. I wish I could teach the sad young of this mealy generation the courage of their confusions.', 12892, 0), (469706, 'When I was 16 the first girl I had a crush on wasn''t interested at all. I liked her from afar for ages, and when I eventually got the courage and told her, and she wasn''t into me.', 74153, 0), (469707, 'In this work I have received the opposition of a number of men who only advocate the unobtainable because the immediately possible is beyond their moral courage, administrative ability, and their political prescience.', 73319, 0), (469708, 'The right response to the non-problem of global warming is to have the courage to do nothing.', 74154, 0), (469709, 'It has been my honor to support and work with President Barack Obama, a man who has brought courage and character to the presidency. President Obama''s strength of character leads him to do the right thing, even when it isn''t the easy thing.', 48859, 0), (469710, 'For the past 25 years as an adoption attorney, I have witnessed the extraordinary courage and compassion of women - from age 14 to 40 - facing unplanned pregnancy. Not once did I believe that the government should interfere with their personal and private decision.', 70026, 0), (469711, 'Therefore, don''t let sinners take courage to think they will be favoured like the thief on the cross; for we see on the other side, they may be like the hardened one, and reproach death itself.', 70847, 0), (469712, 'The foundation of the house of civil rights is in the voices of all the great civil rights leaders and the soul of every person who heard them. It''s in the hands of every person who folded a leaflet for change, and it''s in the courage of every person who changed.', 74155, 0), (469713, 'Discover your own style. Don''t try to repeat what has already been written - have the courage to do your own thing and don''t be afraid to do something different.', 413, 0), (469714, 'My main trick is to work with amazing people. It''s a long and twisty journey, and you need people that really are amazing and have this rare gift of honesty and courage and really open up.', 74156, 0), (469715, 'The only reason I''m in Hollywood is that I don''t have the moral courage to refuse the money.', 57981, 0), (469716, 'In the inhalation and exhalation there is an energy and a lively divine spirit, since He, through his spirit supports the breath of life, giving courage to the people who are in the earth and spirit to those who walk on it.', 74157, 0), (469717, 'I grew up in a very westernised environment and went to a private American school. But my personality was shy and quiet, and I wanted to wear the hijab but didn''t have the courage, as I knew my friends would talk me out of it.', 7837, 0), (469718, 'It would be sad if we lost our instinct and our courage to love and protect.', 67517, 0), (469719, 'As long as the opposition believes the world will stand with Ukraine''s democrat reformers, they will have the leverage and the courage to establish a legitimate republic under the leadership of Viktor Yushchenko.', 72497, 0), (469720, 'He''s nice enough not to want to be associated with a nasty remark but not nice enough not to make it. Lacking the courage of one''s nastiness does not make one nice.', 67237, 0), (469721, 'Iwas not a reader at all, not until I discovered ''The Hobbit.'' That changed my life. It gave me the courage to read. It led me to the ''Lord of the Rings'' series. And once I''d read that, I knew I could read anything because I had just read thousands of pages.', 603, 0), (469722, 'We know the Republicans are happy to keep the country in the dark, and if we Democrats are to recapture the power necessary to assert our values, we must find the energy, courage, creativity and unity to map out a brighter day for the people we sincerely want to serve.', 66709, 0), (469723, 'Hemingway was a jerk. I mean he was really a great jerk. He was a good writer, and he did all sorts of things that I would never have the courage to do, but I don''t think I''d enjoy being in the same room with him. He''s not my kind of person.', 9615, 0), (469724, 'Music was always a big part of my family. Only a few of us had the talent - or the courage - to walk out on a stage.', 70245, 0), (469725, 'It takes a lot of courage as an actor to take time off for family. But family is everything.', 74158, 0), (469726, 'I want to work as hard as I can. But I also want six kids! It takes a lot of courage as an actor to take time off for family. But family is everything.', 74158, 0), (469727, 'I often visit Maria Tatar''s ''The Grimm Reader'' for a cold dose of courage. Her translations come from the Brothers Grimm, whose now-famous collection of ''Kinder- und Hausmarchen'' (''Children''s and Household Tales'') was first published in 1812. The book was not intended for young readers.', 27414, 0), (469728, 'For this equilibrium now in sight, let us trust that mankind, as it has occurred in the greatest periods of its past, will find for itself a new code of ethics, common to all, made of tolerance, of courage, and of faith in the Spirit of men.', 67415, 0), (469729, 'For as long as this nation has known war, we have embraced the heroes it has produced. Americans have rightfully noted the honor and nobility of courage under hostile fire and thanked those who perished in their defense.', 74159, 0), (469730, 'I know what real courage is, and I understand true compassion.', 48537, 0), (469731, 'I like Beryl Bainbridge a great deal, and she is a writer who absolutely demands to be read a second, third, and fourth time. I admire her great courage in leaving so much unsaid and asking the reader to really engage her brain.', 1058, 0), (469732, 'My first and most loved real novel was ''Little Women.'' I identified with the Jo character even though we were opposites. Jo was very strong-minded and brave, and I was shy and kind of a wuss, everyplace but in my own home. I wanted to be Jo. She was my alter ego. I think reading that book gave me courage.', 74160, 0), (469733, 'When I met Bono at the Cannes Film festival while I was there for the film ''United 93,'' he said to me, ''That''s a great film, brother. Thank you for your courage in making it.'' I plotzed.', 74161, 0), (469734, 'Outlining is like putting on training wheels. It gives me the courage to write, but we always go off the outline.', 74162, 0), (469735, 'The eyes of the world are fixed on the U.S. to see if we have the political courage and moral sense to solve our debt crisis.', 71212, 0), (469736, 'But steel bars have never yet kept out a mob it takes something a good deal stronger: human courage backed up by the consciousness of being right. ', 54840, 0), (469737, 'Confronting and undermining the narratives and ideas of extremism must therefore be one of our key tasks. To do this, we must retain the courage of our convictions in the face of extremism.', 74163, 0), (469738, 'Let me start with Yahoo. As we meet today, a Chinese citizen who had the courage to speak his mind on the Internet is in prison because Yahoo chose to share his name and address with the Chinese Government.', 71302, 0), (469739, 'Sadly, far too many politicians in Washington lack the courage to do something to fix our problems. They are worried about the political implications of making the hard choices we so desperately need to cut spending and shrink government.', 73813, 0), (469740, 'My education was dominated by modernist thinkers and artists who taught me that the supreme imperative was courage to face the awful truth, to scorn the soft-minded optimism of religious and secular romantics as well as the corrupt optimism of governments, advertisers, and mechanistic or manipulative revolutionaries.', 17488, 0), (469741, 'The presidents of colleges have to have some courage to step forward. You can''t limit alcohol in college sports, you have to get rid of it.', 7825, 0), (469742, 'I was inspired by my son on the song ''The Most Beautiful People Are Broken.'' Life is an extra challenge for him. But he does it all with such great grace and courage.', 74164, 0), (469743, 'The minute a person whose word means a great deal to others dare to take the open-hearted and courageous way, many others follow.', 15432, 0), (469744, 'I don''t know what kind of courage it took thousands of years ago, but I know how courageous women need to be today.', 2115, 0), (469745, 'Remember in 1973 the same science chatter said that the coming Ice Age is going to occur, we''re going to lose millions of people. And the politicians knew how to solve it, they just didn''t have the courage to solve it; they were going to put coal dust on the Arctic.', 74165, 0), (469746, 'All my life I had feared to-morrow, until I decided to have faith and to live to-day in courage.', 73667, 0), (469747, 'It takes far less courage to kill yourself than it takes to make yourself wake up one more time. It''s harder to stay where you are than to get out. For everyone but you, that is.', 64885, 0), (469748, 'Ronald Reagan''s well documented final battles with Alzheimer''s disease were fought with the same conviction and courage that his many public battles were fought.', 74166, 0), (469749, 'I think that what''s been holding composers back a great deal is that they feel they must have a new style every year. This, in my case, would be hopeless. In fact, it is said that I have no style at all, but that doesn''t matter. I just go on doing, as they say, my thing. I believe this takes a certain courage.', 74167, 0), (469750, 'To bathe a cat takes brute force, perseverance, courage of conviction - and a cat. The last ingredient is usually hardest to come by.', 20563, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469751, 'Design is the courage and brilliance to cover an original and make it different.', 16164, 0), (469752, 'You have to have the courage to face the unexpected. This is the difference between people who do things and people who don''t dare, who don''t dare to live.', 74168, 0), (469753, 'I know this president. And I can tell you that he cares deeply about the next generation of young women in this country - his daughters, and everyone''s daughters. President Obama had the courage to stand with Sandra Fluke. Without hesitation, he defended her right to tell her story.', 72253, 0), (469754, 'Courage is the fear of being thought a coward.', 62879, 0), (469755, 'There can be a fundamental gulf of gracelessness in a human heart which neither our love nor our courage can bridge.', 63398, 0), (469756, 'Success is that old ABC - ability, breaks, and courage.', 11189, 0), (469757, 'There are two great days in a person''s life - the day we are born and the day we discover why.', 18978, 0), (469758, 'It''s sad to know I''m done. But looking back, I''ve got a lot of great memories.', 63991, 0), (469759, 'Behind every great man is a woman rolling her eyes.', 14367, 0), (469760, 'Do the difficult things while they are easy and do the great things while they are small. A journey of a thousand miles must begin with a single step.', 15, 0), (469761, 'People who think they know everything are a great annoyance to those of us who do.', 988, 0), (469762, 'Great minds discuss ideas average minds discuss events small minds discuss people. ', 141, 0), (469763, 'Great things are done by a series of small things brought together.', 89, 0), (469764, 'No dream is too big. No challenge is too great. Nothing we want for our future is beyond our reach.', 64643, 0), (469765, 'Some are born great, some achieve greatness, and some have greatness thrust upon them.', 13, 0), (469766, 'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn''t so great.', 72235, 0), (469767, 'A little thought and a little kindness are often worth more than a great deal of money.', 485, 0), (469768, 'Only great minds can afford a simple style.', 952, 0), (469769, 'Life is either a great adventure or nothing.', 701, 0), (469770, 'Simply enjoy life and the great pleasures that come with it.', 74169, 0), (469771, 'The greatest weapon against stress is our ability to choose one thought over another.', 1782, 0), (469772, 'On some great and glorious day the plain folks of the land will reach their heart''s desire at last, and the White House will be adorned by a downright moron.', 411, 0), (469773, 'Small aim is a crime have great aim. ', 1798, 0), (469774, 'The greatest accomplishment is not in never falling, but in rising again after you fall.', 5571, 0), (469775, 'Great thoughts speak only to the thoughtful mind, but great actions speak to all mankind.', 1674, 0), (469776, 'I''d rather attempt to do something great and fail than to attempt to do nothing and succeed.', 1935, 0), (469777, 'Who''s my hero? That''s a great question... Well, I think my dad is my hero, because he''s someone I look up to every day.', 66949, 0), (469778, 'Veterans are a symbol of what makes our nation great, and we must never forget all they have done to ensure our freedom.', 69511, 0), (469779, 'If you cannot do great things, do small things in a great way.', 1187, 0), (469780, 'Great achievement is usually born of great sacrifice, and is never the result of selfishness.', 1187, 0), (469781, 'The greatness of a nation can be judged by the way its animals are treated.', 32, 0), (469782, 'A great figure or physique is nice, but it''s self-confidence that makes someone really sexy.', 74170, 0), (469783, 'Passion is one great force that unleashes creativity, because if you''re passionate about something, then you''re more willing to take risks.', 25711, 0), (469784, 'There have been so many great moments, and I feel so blessed every day.', 74171, 0), (469785, 'There is no pain so great as the memory of joy in present grief.', 1882, 0), (469786, 'We will make America strong again. We will make America proud again. We will make America safe again. And we will make America great again.', 64643, 0), (469787, 'Pray that your loneliness may spur you into finding something to live for, great enough to die for.', 851, 0), (469788, 'All truly great thoughts are conceived by walking.', 11, 0), (469789, 'It is a rough road that leads to the heights of greatness.', 65434, 0), (469790, 'The most important thing is to try and inspire people so that they can be great in whatever they want to do.', 44746, 0), (469791, 'The essence of all beautiful art, all great art, is gratitude.', 11, 0), (469792, 'I feel like life is really short, and it''s important to enjoy yourself and embrace whatever comes your way, whether it''s a challenging day or a great day, just welcome it with open arms. No matter who you are, you can''t escape challenges; they are part of life.', 18360, 0), (469793, 'Those who dare to fail miserably can achieve greatly.', 1680, 0), (469794, 'Step with care and great tact, and remember that Life''s a Great Balancing Act.', 3, 0), (469795, 'I am a great admirer of mystery and magic. Look at this life - all mystery and magic.', 48153, 0), (469796, 'What wisdom can you find that is greater than kindness?', 1372, 0), (469797, 'Great things are done when men and mountains meet.', 221, 0), (469798, 'The great art of life is sensation, to feel that we exist, even in pain.', 62558, 0), (469799, 'Silence is one of the great arts of conversation.', 1306, 0), (469800, 'In October, a maple tree before your window lights up your room like a great lamp. Even on cloudy days, its presence helps to dispel the gloom.', 1069, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469801, 'The harder the struggle, the more glorious the triumph. Self-realization demands very great struggle.', 62960, 0), (469802, 'I have always loved fashion because it''s a great way to express your mood. And I''m definitely a shoe lover. The right pair of shoes can change the feel of an outfit, and even change how a woman feels about herself. A woman can wear confidence on her feet with a high stiletto, or slip into weekend comfort with a soft ballet flat.', 55411, 0), (469803, 'Great dancers are not great because of their technique, they are great because of their passion.', 1209, 0), (469804, 'To me, there''s no great chef without a great team.', 68041, 0), (469805, 'I tell a student that the most important class you can take is technique. A great chef is first a great technician. ''If you are a jeweler, or a surgeon or a cook, you have to know the trade in your hand. You have to learn the process. You learn it through endless repetition until it belongs to you.', 43897, 0), (469806, 'A man''s worth is no greater than his ambitions.', 267, 0), (469807, 'You can''t build a great building on a weak foundation. You must have a solid foundation if you''re going to have a strong superstructure.', 197, 0), (469808, 'Today''s a beautiful day, and yesterday was a beautiful day, so that means it''s a great life.', 70505, 0), (469809, 'The hottest place in Hell is reserved for those who remain neutral in times of great moral conflict.', 21767, 0), (469810, 'Belief in oneself and knowing who you are, I mean, that''s the foundation for everything great.', 8650, 0), (469811, 'Nothing great in the world has ever been accomplished without passion.', 2787, 0), (469812, 'The point is that when I see a sunset or a waterfall or something, for a split second it''s so great, because for a little bit I''m out of my brain, and it''s got nothing to do with me. I''m not trying to figure it out, you know what I mean? And I wonder if I can somehow find a way to maintain that mind stillness.', 23824, 0), (469813, 'Every great and deep difficulty bears in itself its own solution. It forces us to change our thinking in order to find it.', 2826, 0), (469814, 'The comfort zone is the great enemy to creativity; moving beyond it necessitates intuition, which in turn configures new perspectives and conquers fears.', 31314, 0), (469815, 'One of the greatest diseases is to be nobody to anybody.', 70, 0), (469816, 'Scientists dream about doing great things. Engineers do them.', 2239, 0), (469817, 'We want to do a lot of stuff we''re not in great shape. We didn''t get a good night''s sleep. We''re a little depressed. Coffee solves all these problems in one delightful little cup. ', 2195, 0), (469818, 'You have the ability to choose which way you want to go. You have to believe great things are going to happen in your life. Do everything you can - prepare, pray and achieve - to make it happen.', 1793, 0), (469819, 'My only fault is that I don''t realize how great I really am.', 1751, 0), (469820, 'I have great faith in fools self-confidence my friends call it. ', 49, 0), (469821, 'A lot of people, when a guy scores a lot of goals, think, ''He''s a great player'', because a goal is very important, but a great player is a player who can do everything on the field. He can do assists, encourage his colleagues, give them confidence to go forward. It is someone who, when a team does not do well, becomes one of the leaders.', 12296, 0), (469822, 'I look at my father. He is one of my heroes. He is such an incredible, classy man. He was such a great father and such a great husband in so many ways, and we lived through some pretty tough times losing my mom. When I see all that he did, I think, ''Wow, that''s a really wonderful man.''', 68524, 0), (469823, 'Software is a great combination between artistry and engineering.', 1133, 0), (469824, 'I have a great relationship with the Mexican people.', 64643, 0), (469825, 'A great accomplishment shouldn''t be the end of the road, just the starting point for the next leap forward.', 25461, 0), (469826, 'I always believed that when you follow your heart or your gut, when you really follow the things that feel great to you, you can never lose, because settling is the worst feeling in the world.', 7387, 0), (469827, 'Success doesn''t necessarily come from breakthrough innovation but from flawless execution. A great strategy alone won''t win a game or a battle the win comes from basic blocking and tackling. ', 66796, 0), (469828, 'The conscious mind may be compared to a fountain playing in the sun and falling back into the great subterranean pool of subconscious from which it rises.', 555, 0), (469829, 'The planter, the farmer, the mechanic, and the laborer... form the great body of the people of the United States, they are the bone and sinew of the country men who love liberty and desire nothing but equal rights and equal laws.', 2245, 0), (469830, 'The greatest way to live with honor in this world is to be what we pretend to be.', 1595, 0), (469831, 'It''s so great to find that one special person you want to annoy for the rest of your life.', 2210, 0), (469832, 'Great leaders are almost always great simplifiers, who can cut through argument, debate and doubt, to offer a solution everybody can understand.', 1749, 0), (469833, 'Perseverance is a great element of success. If you only knock long enough and loud enough at the gate, you are sure to wake up somebody.', 147, 0), (469834, 'Her angel''s face, As the great eye of heaven shined bright, And made a sunshine in the shady place.', 3761, 0), (469835, 'There''s something so great about being with your nephew and, when you''re tired, just handing him off back to your sister.', 74172, 0), (469836, 'An entire nation, it seemed, was standing in one long breadline, desperate for even the barest essentials. It was a crisis of monumental proportions. It was known as the Great Depression.', 69235, 0), (469837, 'If the great American people will only keep their temper, on both sides of the line, the troubles will come to an end, and the question which now distracts the country will be settled just as surely as all other difficulties of like character which have originated in this government have been adjusted.', 1012, 0), (469838, 'Those who want to reap the benefits of this great nation must bear the fatigue of supporting it.', 1131, 0), (469839, 'I love my iPhone it''s great to have a camera around all the time. ', 68528, 0), (469840, 'When you get to know a lot of people, you make a great discovery. You find that no one group has a monopoly on looks, brains, goodness or anything else. It takes all the people - black and white, Catholic, Jewish and Protestant, recent immigrants and Mayflower descendants - to make up America.', 346, 0), (469841, 'Pursue one great decisive aim with force and determination.', 2677, 0), (469842, 'Education then, beyond all other devices of human origin, is the great equalizer of the conditions of men, the balance-wheel of the social machinery.', 2053, 0), (469843, 'Synergy is what happens when one plus one equals ten or a hundred or even a thousand! It''s the profound result when two or more respectful human beings determine to go beyond their preconceived ideas to meet a great challenge.', 10390, 0), (469844, 'Coffee and smoking are the last great addictions.', 66874, 0), (469845, 'Great companies that build an enduring brand have an emotional relationship with customers that has no barrier. And that emotional relationship is on the most important characteristic, which is trust.', 19506, 0), (469846, 'To live alone is the fate of all great souls.', 1304, 0), (469847, 'I find the great thing in this world is not so much where we stand, as in what direction we are moving: To reach the port of heaven, we must sail sometimes with the wind and sometimes against it - but we must sail, and not drift, nor lie at anchor.', 24754, 0), (469848, 'Never quit believing that you can develop in life. Never give up. Don''t deny the inward spirit that provides the drive to accomplish great things in life.', 68225, 0), (469849, 'A great city, whose image dwells in the memory of man, is the type of some great idea. Rome represents conquest; Faith hovers over the towers of Jerusalem; and Athens embodies the pre-eminent quality of the antique world, Art.', 1827, 0), (469850, 'I would not dare to say that there is a direct relation between mathematics and madness, but there is no doubt that great mathematicians suffer from maniacal characteristics, delirium, and symptoms of schizophrenia.', 71867, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469851, 'Great theatre is about challenging how we think and encouraging us to fantasize about a world we aspire to.', 67567, 0), (469852, 'The Great Depression, like most other periods of severe unemployment, was produced by government mismanagement rather than by any inherent instability of the private economy.', 16707, 0), (469853, 'Check your ego at the door. The ego can be the great success inhibitor. It can kill opportunities, and it can kill success.', 11331, 0), (469854, 'There may be a great fire in our hearts, yet no one ever comes to warm himself at it, and the passers-by see only a wisp of smoke.', 89, 0), (469855, 'In reading the lives of great men, I found that the first victory they won was over themselves... self-discipline with all of them came first.', 16121, 0), (469856, 'Nothing beats a great smile.', 74173, 0), (469857, 'It''s very hard to find true friends when your life is a bumpy ride full of twists and turns. But, I''m glad that amidst all the ramblings in my life I have managed to win some great friends.', 69674, 0), (469858, 'There is a dark side in all of us. And for us ''bad'' people, the bad side dominates. I think there is a great sadness in villains, and I have tried to put that across. We cannot stop ourselves doing what we are doing.', 61247, 0), (469859, 'One sees great things from the valley only small things from the peak. ', 67663, 0), (469860, 'Every great story seems to begin with a snake.', 67437, 0), (469861, 'Whatever you want to do, if you want to be great at it, you have to love it and be able to make sacrifices for it.', 74, 0), (469862, 'If it wasn''t hard, everyone would do it. It''s the hard that makes it great.', 13172, 0), (469863, 'You have to come to your closed doors before you get to your open doors... What if you knew you had to go through 32 closed doors before you got to your open door? Well, then you''d come to closed door number eight and you''d think, ''Great, I got another one out of the way''... Keep moving forward.', 3956, 0), (469864, 'Harmony makes small things grow, lack of it makes great things decay.', 4812, 0), (469865, 'In framing a government which is to be administered by men over men, the great difficulty lies in this: you must first enable the government to control the governed; and in the next place, oblige it to control itself.', 16733, 0), (469866, 'Great journalism will always attract readers. The words, pictures and graphics that are the stuff of journalism have to be brilliantly packaged; they must feed the mind and move the heart.', 15116, 0), (469867, 'Someone told me that having a baby is like having your heart walking around outside of your body, and I didn''t understand it until I had a baby. Now, like, everything he does literally crushes my heart. In a great way. And then if he''s in pain, it''s like my whole endeavor is to make sure he''s not in pain.', 68450, 0), (469868, 'Growth is the great separator between those who succeed and those who do not. When I see a person beginning to separate themselves from the pack, it''s almost always due to personal growth.', 1810, 0), (469869, 'Racing is a great mania to which one must sacrifice everything, without reticence, without hesitation.', 71388, 0), (469870, 'All great change in America begins at the dinner table.', 1727, 0), (469871, 'Sunrise offered a very beautiful spectacle; the water was quite unruffled, but the motion communicated by the tides was so great that, although there was not a breath of air stirring, the sea heaved slowly with a grand and majestic motion.', 74174, 0), (469872, 'The great question that has never been answered, and which I have not yet been able to answer, despite my thirty years of research into the feminine soul, is ''What does a woman want?''', 555, 0), (469873, 'We are all faced with a series of great opportunities brilliantly disguised as impossible situations.', 1789, 0), (469874, 'America''s fighting men and women sacrifice much to ensure that our great nation stays free. We owe a debt of gratitude to the soldiers that have paid the ultimate price for this cause, as well as for those who are blessed enough to return from the battlefield unscathed.', 74175, 0), (469875, 'The boy who is going to make a great man must not make up his mind merely to overcome a thousand obstacles, but to win in spite of a thousand repulses and defeats.', 1674, 0), (469876, 'The great advantage of a hotel is that it is a refuge from home life.', 266, 0), (469877, 'A wedding, a great wedding, is just a blast. A celebration of romance and community and love... What is unfun about that? Nothing.', 28276, 0), (469878, 'Awards are great, as you get to meet up with friends and colleagues from your industry - a sort of reunion.', 68266, 0), (469879, 'In spite of everything I shall rise again: I will take up my pencil, which I have forsaken in my great discouragement, and I will go on with my drawing.', 89, 0), (469880, 'To vilify a great man is the readiest way in which a little man can himself attain greatness.', 49, 0), (469881, 'In New York it seems like there''s no Monday or Saturday or Sunday. The town is always moving. The vibe is great.', 68173, 0), (469882, 'Life is made up, not of great sacrifices or duties, but of little things, in which smiles and kindness, and small obligations given habitually, are what preserve the heart and secure comfort.', 13416, 0), (469883, 'The heights by great men reached and kept were not attained by sudden flight, but they, while their companions slept, were toiling upward in the night.', 147, 0), (469884, 'Man becomes great exactly in the degree in which he works for the welfare of his fellow-men.', 32, 0), (469885, 'I am an old man and have known a great many troubles, but most of them never happened.', 286, 0), (469886, 'A man is great by deeds, not by birth.', 25555, 0), (469887, 'Going to the gym is great for your body, but it''s also great for your mind.', 72004, 0), (469888, 'To become truly great, one has to stand with people, not above them.', 48659, 0), (469889, 'Faith is the great cop-out, the great excuse to evade the need to think and evaluate evidence. Faith is belief in spite of, even perhaps because of, the lack of evidence.', 1716, 0), (469890, 'The reason we have poverty is that we have no imagination. There are a great many people accumulating what they think is vast wealth, but it''s only money... they don''t know how to enjoy it, because they have no imagination.', 45466, 0), (469891, 'Little minds are tamed and subdued by misfortune but great minds rise above them. ', 944, 0), (469892, 'Great countries need to secure their border for national security purposes, for economic purposes and for rule of law purposes.', 68245, 0), (469893, 'I am the greatest, I said that even before I knew I was.', 1751, 0), (469894, 'Curiosity about life in all of its aspects, I think, is still the secret of great creative people.', 64007, 0), (469895, 'The ocean is a central image. It is the symbolism of a great journey.', 70718, 0), (469896, 'To be a great motorbike racer, the most important thing is passion for the bike.', 70738, 0), (469897, 'The best way a mentor can prepare another leader is to expose him or her to other great people.', 1810, 0), (469898, 'Innovation comes out of great human ingenuity and very personal passions.', 47130, 0), (469899, 'Life seeks life and loves life. The opening of a catkin of a willow, in the flight of the butterfly, in the chirping of a tree-toad or the sweep of an eagle - my life loves to see how others live, exults in their joy, and so far is partner in their great concern.', 31769, 0), (469900, 'Life is short, youth is finite, and opportunities endless. Have you found the intersection of your passion and the potential for world-shaping positive impact? If you don''t have a great idea of your own, there are plenty of great teams that need you - unknown startups and established teams in giant companies alike.', 68138, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469901, 'Great men are like eagles, and build their nest on some lofty solitude.', 1304, 0), (469902, 'I''m bored'' is a useless thing to say. You live in a great, big, vast world that you''ve seen none percent of.', 536, 0), (469903, 'The great musicians are those who can reach people, who can make people feel something.', 74176, 0), (469904, 'We are descended from a people whose government was founded on liberty; our glorious forefathers of Great Britain made liberty the foundation of everything. That country is become a great, mighty, and splendid nation; not because their government is strong and energetic, but, sir, because liberty is its direct end and foundation.', 3269, 0), (469905, 'No crime is so great as daring to excel.', 3621, 0), (469906, 'I truly believe in positive synergy, that your positive mindset gives you a more hopeful outlook, and belief that you can do something great means you will do something great.', 70811, 0), (469907, 'The world runs on individuals pursuing their self interests. The great achievements of civilization have not come from government bureaus. Einstein didn''t construct his theory under order from a, from a bureaucrat. Henry Ford didn''t revolutionize the automobile industry that way.', 16707, 0), (469908, 'Life is a great big canvas throw all the paint you can at it. ', 1181, 0), (469909, 'In an individual sport, yes, you have to win titles. Baseball''s different. But basketball, hockey? One person can control the tempo of a game, can completely alter the momentum of a series. There''s a lot of great individual talent.', 44746, 0), (469910, 'Let us not listen to those who think we ought to be angry with our enemies, and who believe this to be great and manly. Nothing is so praiseworthy, nothing so clearly shows a great and noble soul, as clemency and readiness to forgive.', 1306, 0), (469911, 'Governing a great nation is like cooking a small fish - too much handling will spoil it.', 15, 0), (469912, 'A great man is one who leaves others at a loss after he is gone.', 3087, 0), (469913, 'Great personal style is an extreme curiosity about yourself.', 67408, 0), (469914, 'Life is not an easy matter... You cannot live through it without falling into frustration and cynicism unless you have before you a great idea which raises you above personal misery, above weakness, above all kinds of perfidy and baseness.', 1626, 0), (469915, 'I believe the first test of a truly great man is in his humility.', 485, 0), (469916, 'Fantasies can be great, but we shouldn''t make the wedding a fantasy, because the wedding is the gateway to married life. It shouldn''t be a moment of illusion; it should be a moment of preparation.', 639, 0), (469917, 'From the beginning, the camera and I were great friends. It loves me, and I love it.', 15469, 0), (469918, 'Gray is great. People think gray is a neutral, but I think it''s such a moody, intense, dramatic and sexy color. It''s very sleek.', 10716, 0), (469919, 'In real estate, you make 10% of your money because you''re a genius and 90% because you catch a great wave.', 74177, 0), (469920, 'Always in life bad times will lead to great times.', 73706, 0), (469921, 'It would be doing me great injustice to think that I have any feeling of indifference to my country; I have more reason than anyone to feel, every day of my life, the value of the blood which flows in my veins, and it is only from prudence that at times I abstain from showing how proud I am of it.', 19731, 0), (469922, 'Male and female represent the two sides of the great radical dualism. But in fact they are perpetually passing into one another. Fluid hardens to solid, solid rushes to fluid. There is no wholly masculine man, no purely feminine woman.', 2792, 0), (469923, 'The greatest mistake you can make in life is continually fearing that you''ll make one.', 4, 0), (469924, 'To accomplish great things we must first dream, then visualize, then plan... believe... act!', 877, 0), (469925, 'Great necessities call out great virtues.', 5280, 0), (469926, 'Great things are not accomplished by those who yield to trends and fads and popular opinion.', 382, 0), (469927, 'Every great achievement is but a small peak in the mountain range of contributions.', 74178, 0), (469928, 'I am more afraid of my own heart than of the pope and all his cardinals. I have within me the great pope, Self.', 1746, 0), (469929, 'A great social success is a pretty girl who plays her cards as carefully as if she were plain.', 97, 0), (469930, 'To have a great idea, have a lot of them.', 1673, 0), (469931, 'I''m not perfect. I''m never going to be. And that''s the great thing about living the Christian life and trying to live by faith, is you''re trying to get better every day. You''re trying to improve.', 4052, 0), (469932, 'Great men are they who see that spiritual is stronger than any material force - that thoughts rule the world.', 760, 0), (469933, 'Small deeds done are better than great deeds planned.', 2148, 0), (469934, 'I am concerned for the security of our great Nation; not so much because of any threat from without, but because of the insidious forces working from within.', 2273, 0), (469935, 'Do you wish to be great? Then begin by being. Do you desire to construct a vast and lofty fabric? Think first about the foundations of humility. The higher your structure is to be, the deeper must be its foundation.', 63060, 0), (469936, 'What''s great about this country is that America started the tradition where the richest consumers buy essentially the same things as the poorest. You can be watching TV and see Coca-Cola, and you can know that the President drinks Coke. Liz Taylor drinks Coke, and just think, you can drink Coke, too.', 321, 0), (469937, 'No great artist ever sees things as they really are. If he did, he would cease to be an artist.', 40, 0), (469938, 'The great fights with your strongest rivals are always the biggest motivation. When you win easily it''s not the same taste.', 70738, 0), (469939, 'The past is a great place and I don''t want to erase it or to regret it, but I don''t want to be its prisoner either.', 20225, 0), (469940, 'I love love, and I love life. I love. I just love. It''s just great. It''s the most enduring element we have is love.', 68179, 0), (469941, 'Innovation in an existing company is not just the sum of great technology, key acquisitions, or smart people. Corporate innovation needs a culture that matches and supports it.', 68928, 0), (469942, 'Great ambition, the desire of real superiority, of leading and directing, seems to be altogether peculiar to man, and speech is the great instrument of ambition.', 2485, 0), (469943, 'Believe deep down in your heart that you''re destined to do great things.', 11184, 0), (469944, 'To do a great right do a little wrong.', 13, 0), (469945, 'Until the great mass of the people shall be filled with the sense of responsibility for each other''s welfare, social justice can never be attained.', 701, 0), (469946, 'A great day in New York would be to wake up, get a cup of coffee and head up to Central Park for a nice walk. Then I''d go down to the East Village and stroll around. After that, maybe I''d go check out a museum or catch an indie film at the Angelika.', 68524, 0), (469947, 'Great minds have purposes others have wishes. ', 944, 0), (469948, 'I think it''s wonderful when a love story begins with a great deal of romance and affection, passion and excitement, that''s how it should be. But I don''t necessarily know that it''s the wisest thing in the world to expect that it ends there, or that it should, 30 years down the road, still look as it did on the night of your first kiss.', 20, 0), (469949, 'Laws control the lesser man... Right conduct controls the greater one.', 286, 0), (469950, 'It''s hard to be humble, when you''re as great as I am.', 1751, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (469951, 'Great leaders don''t need to act tough. Their confidence and humility serve to underscore their toughness.', 19485, 0), (469952, 'Rice is great if you''re really hungry and want to eat two thousand of something.', 27687, 0), (469953, 'There''s a great metaphor that one of my doctors uses: If a fish is swimming in a dirty tank and it gets sick, do you take it to the vet and amputate the fin? No, you clean the water. So, I cleaned up my system. By eating organic raw greens, nuts and healthy fats, I am flooding my body with enzymes, vitamins and oxygen.', 906, 0), (469954, 'A battle lost or won is easily described, understood, and appreciated, but the moral growth of a great nation requires reflection, as well as observation, to appreciate it.', 7432, 0), (469955, 'I was a great student. I was good at everything.', 64643, 0), (469956, 'The sound of a kiss is not so loud as that of a cannon, but its echo lasts a great deal longer.', 24754, 0), (469957, 'A great tailor is like a great personal trainer - they tailor that suit to your natural physique.', 22898, 0), (469958, 'The digital camera is a great invention because it allows us to reminisce. Instantly.', 2315, 0), (469959, 'We come nearest to the great when we are great in humility.', 430, 0), (469960, 'Great leaders don''t rush to blame. They instinctively look for solutions.', 61422, 0), (469961, 'Fables should be taught as fables, myths as myths, and miracles as poetic fantasies. To teach superstitions as truths is a most terrible thing. The child mind accepts and believes them, and only through great pain and perhaps tragedy can he be in after years relieved of them.', 30852, 0), (469962, 'For a true writer, each book should be a new beginning where he tries again for something that is beyond attainment. He should always try for something that has never been done or that others have tried and failed. Then sometimes, with great luck, he will succeed.', 110, 0), (469963, 'My greatest point is my persistence. I never give up in a match. However down I am, I fight until the last ball. My list of matches shows that I have turned a great many so-called irretrievable defeats into victories.', 74179, 0), (469964, 'The demand to be loved is the greatest of all arrogant presumptions.', 11, 0), (469965, 'There are many alternatives to embryonic stem cell research, alternatives with great potential. We need to support these and oppose creating life for the sole purpose of destroying it.', 70322, 0), (469966, 'Denied anything ardently desired, the individual or state will argue and parley just so long - then, if the impelling motive be sufficiently great, will cast aside every rule and break down every acquired inhibition, plunging viciously after the object wished; all the more fantastically savage because of previous repression.', 1060, 0), (469967, 'I plant a lot of trees. I am a great believer in planting things for future generations. I loathe the now culture where you just live for today.', 28900, 0), (469968, 'It is not the clear-sighted who rule the world. Great achievements are accomplished in a blessed, warm fog.', 1241, 0), (469969, 'I woke up and realized life is great and people are awesome and life is worth living.', 66791, 0), (469970, 'Grown men can learn from very little children for the hearts of little children are pure. Therefore, the Great Spirit may show to them many things which older people miss.', 2576, 0), (469971, 'I think it''s great to dress up and play on all the girly features.', 746, 0), (469972, 'My childhood was great, honestly. I have all these incredible memories of my childhood. I was an only child. I always had all my cousins around. I had my grandparents around. I had my parents around. I had my uncles around - whatever.', 67552, 0), (469973, 'Attachment is the great fabricator of illusions reality can be attained only by someone who is detached. ', 1662, 0), (469974, 'Great things are accomplished by talented people who believe they will accomplish them.', 19589, 0), (469975, 'If you don''t know how great this country is, I know someone who does; Russia.', 35, 0), (469976, 'A great city is not to be confounded with a populous one.', 1116, 0), (469977, 'Shopping with friends is a great way of still enjoying the thrill of the chase without having to make a purchase. It can also be a real bonding opportunity. Helping your friend find something nice is just as rewarding as helping yourself.', 173, 0), (469978, 'A great book begins with an idea; a great life, with a determination.', 1682, 0), (469979, 'Great people have great values and great ethics.', 11220, 0), (469980, 'The practice of charity will bind us - will bind all men in one great brotherhood.', 11167, 0), (469981, 'Man as an individual is a genius. But men in the mass form the headless monster, a great, brutish idiot that goes where prodded.', 454, 0), (469982, 'Living is no laughing matter: you must live with great seriousness like a squirrel for example - I mean without looking for something beyond and above living, I mean living must be your whole occupation.', 10321, 0), (469983, 'I have to tell you, I''m proudest of my life off the court. There will always be great basketball players who bounce that little round ball, but my proudest moments are affecting people''s lives, effecting change, being a role model in the community.', 67024, 0), (469984, 'It''s not like a boss and artist relationship; it''s like a big brother to a younger brother relationship, and he''s a great guy. So big shout-out to Akon and the Konvict Muzik crowd.', 73438, 0), (469985, 'Ambition is an idol, on whose wings great minds are carried only to extreme; to be sublimely great or to be nothing.', 39554, 0), (469986, 'The youngest children have a great capacity for empathy and altruism. There''s a recent study that shows even 14-month-olds will climb across a bunch of cushions and go across a room to give yo